{"id": "143719", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143719", "title": "Awakening", "text": "Awakening is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThe wielder will kneel down and strike themselves in the back with the flail twice, inflicting damage equal to 13% of their maximum &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; with each hit. The whipping animation is performed over roughly 8.5 seconds, and has a small window of interruption before and after the first whip. For the next 120 seconds, all offensive &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt; cast by the player will inflict 25% more damage. The buff is not tied to the weapon, and persists after switching away from the Rose of Ariandel. The buff duration cannot be extended by equipping the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nThis skill greatly improves the hitting power of all offensive Miracles, but does not improve the strength of buffs or heals. As such, it is only beneficial when casting spells like &lt;a href=\"Lifehunt%20Scythe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lifehunt Scythe&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, and will not benefit spells like &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Oath%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sacred Oath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Replenishment%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Replenishment&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Soothing%20Sunlight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soothing Sunlight&lt;/a&gt;. As the HP cost of the skill can be easily recovered through the use of healing Miracles, it is a boon for any build that relies heavily on offensive Miracles rather than on weapons.\nOnline gameplay.\nThis skill's greatest strength is that it can be combined with other spell-boosting equipment such as &lt;a href=\"Morne%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Morne's Ring&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Sun%27s%20First%20Born\"&gt;Ring of the Sun's First Born&lt;/a&gt;, increasing the maximum possible damage dealt on a build. With the proper setup, it can greatly increase the lethality of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;-traded Miracles such as a point-blank &lt;a href=\"Sunlight%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sunlight Spear&lt;/a&gt;, potentially killing other players in a single cast.\nCare must be taken when performing this skill though, as it takes several seconds, and the self-inflicted damage can be seen by all players in the world. It should only be activated when one can be guaranteed safety for several seconds."}
