{"id": "9451", "revid": "48110874", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9451", "title": "Balder Knight", "text": "Balder Knights are\u00a0 in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nBalder Knights are located in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Parish\"&gt;Undead Parish&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral Information.\nThere are three varieties of Balder Knights: Side Sword, Rapier, and Crossbow. Those wielding rapiers are stronger and drop more &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0\nThe Rapier variant of the Balder Knight can switch stances, holding its weapon at chest level, pointed at the player. While its stance is altered thus, the Balder Knight can parry.\u00a0\nLore.\nBalder Knights came to Lordran in large numbers along with their king, &lt;a href=\"Knight%20King%20Rendal\"&gt;Knight King Rendal&lt;/a&gt;, seeking a cure for the &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; curse. However, none were able to defeat the Iron Golem, and they ended up as &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollows&lt;/a&gt; in the Undead Parish or Sen's Fortress.\nIt is possible that &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Soldier%20%28Sword%29\"&gt;at least one Balder Knight&lt;/a&gt; managed to enter Anor Londo, becoming a member of the Darkmoon covenant. \nStrategy.\nBalder Knights have a fair amount of &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;, and are a considerable threat to new characters. Even one-on-one, they can be very dangerous.\nAny ranged attack is useful against them, but they are fast and will close the gap quickly. &lt;a href=\"Firebomb\"&gt;Firebomb&lt;/a&gt;s can be very useful in defeating them.\nCritical attacks, such as the &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;Parry and Riposte&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;, are exceedingly efficient methods to dispatch these enemies.\nEnemy Information.\nDefenses.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nCrossbow=\nSword=\nRapier=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
