{"id": "7846", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7846", "title": "Balder Set", "text": "The Balder Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Medium Armor Set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nPlot.\nWorn by &lt;a href=\"Balder%20Knight\"&gt;Balder Knight&lt;/a&gt;s. Also worn by an unnamed NPC that spawns in &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Dark Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThis set offers high &lt;a href=\"physical%20defense\"&gt;physical defense&lt;/a&gt;s. However, it offers much lower &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; resistances. It is one of the &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;lighter&lt;/a&gt; medium armor sets. It offers high defenses for where it can be farmed early on in the game."}
{"id": "3212", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3212", "title": "Balder Shield", "text": "The Balder Shield is a &lt;a href=\"medium%20shield\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Balder Shield is an uncommon drop from &lt;a href=\"Balder%20Knight\"&gt;Balder Knight&lt;/a&gt;s. Only knights actually using the shield will drop it - Balder Knights using the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Buckler\"&gt;Buckler&lt;/a&gt; will drop that instead. It can also be purchased from the &lt;a href=\"Crestfallen%20Merchant\"&gt;Crestfallen Merchant&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt; for 4,000 &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Balder Shield has the second-highest base &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; of all medium shields, and is therefore one of the strongest &lt;a href=\"shields\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt; against &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; attacks early in the game. Later on, the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight%20Shield\"&gt;Silver Knight Shield&lt;/a&gt; exceeds it in most respects, but is also &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;heavier&lt;/a&gt; and has slightly higher &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; requirements, making the Balder Shield remain an all-around good choice into the endgame if upgraded.\nIt has a medium deflection and normal &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; speed. When &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt;, its &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; is 22.\nResistance Defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of &lt;a href=\"status\"&gt;status&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking."}
{"id": "3347", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3347", "title": "Balder Side Sword", "text": "The Balder Side Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Balder Side Sword is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Balder%20Knight\"&gt;Balder Knight&lt;/a&gt;s that wield it the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Parish\"&gt;Undead Parish&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt; at a 1% drop rate.\nSince the drop rate is low, using the &lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Gold%20Serpent%20Ring\"&gt;Covetous Gold Serpent Ring&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Symbol%20of%20Avarice\"&gt;Symbol of Avarice&lt;/a&gt; and 10 &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20%28gameplay%20mechanic%29\"&gt;liquid Humanity&lt;/a&gt; to get to 410 &lt;a href=\"Item%20Discovery\"&gt;Item Discovery&lt;/a&gt; is recommended. As the sword is available long before any of the item discovery boosting gear it may be preferable to use a substitute weapon until the Covetous Gold Serpent Ring is obtained.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Balder Side Sword improves on the already good straight sword &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; by replacing the usual strong attacks with a unique thrust combo that has greatly increased damage, at the cost of losing the advancing slash of standard two-handed straight swords. It is also significantly longer than other straight swords. It's long reach and powerful thrusts makes it a great weapon for &lt;a href=\"Counter%20Attack\"&gt;counter attacking&lt;/a&gt;, especially when paired with the &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile the standard &lt;a href=\"Longsword\"&gt;Longsword&lt;/a&gt; can out damage it on quality builds, the Balder Side Sword's low &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement and heavy focus on &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; scaling allows it to reach similar damage to most other straight swords in the game at a lower stat investment. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
