{"id": "2076", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2076", "title": "Bandit", "text": "The Bandit is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe Bandit specializes in hard-hitting physical attacks, and is great with weapons such as axes and straight swords. The starting battle axe is great for the game\u2019s early areas, where dealing with enemies in as few hits as possible is important. Their high endurance and strength will mean that of all classes they deal the most damage at the beginning of the game. The Bandit\u2019s magic stats are very poor, so using any kind of magic isn\u2019t an option without spending a lot of levels on one of those stats. Their starting armor also isn\u2019t great, but you will have no trouble equipping better armor and shields as you find them.\nBandits begin as a mid-rolling class with their starting equipment and armor, but removing gauntlets or leg armor can allow them to fast-roll at the start of the game."}
{"id": "2443", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2443", "title": "Bandit's Knife", "text": "The Bandit's Knife is a &lt;a href=\"Daggers\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Bandit's Knife deals low damage, but makes up for it in terms of critical rate. In terms of its &lt;a href=\"Critical%20attack\"&gt;Critical Modifier&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"riposte\"&gt;riposte&lt;/a&gt;, the Bandit's Knife is second only to the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Silver%20Tracer\"&gt;Dark Silver Tracer&lt;/a&gt;. Do not mistake a high Critical Modifier for dealing the most damage on crits, as weapons with high base damage and scaling will perform better. The Bandit's Knife deals &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; at a rate of 30 per strike, and can also be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; with weapon buffs. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that: "}
{"id": "45752", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45752", "title": "Bandit's Knife (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Bandit's Knife is a &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Bandit's Knife exchanges direct damage for &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up from a fast moveset. It loses basically no bleed buildup on infusions while gaining some damage.\nThe rapid attack speed and bleed makes the Bandit's Knife an effective weapon in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; when trying to bleed opponents, particularly when used with another bleed weapon. Bleed causes 200 damage and a lingering effect oh reduced stamina, thus slowling down the opponent. This can create advantage that can be used to aggress.\nOutside of PvP, the weapon is far less potent due to the negligible impact of bleed's lingering effects on normal enemies."}
{"id": "132921", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132921", "title": "Bandit's Knife (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Bandit's Knife is a &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Bandit's Knife sacrifices some of the &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;daggers&lt;/a&gt;' high crit damage to provide &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up. This makes it an excellent choice to buff with &lt;a href=\"Carthus%20Rouge\"&gt;Carthus Rouge&lt;/a&gt; or to infuse with a &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Gem\"&gt;Blood Gem&lt;/a&gt;. As with its previous incarnations, the rapid cuts can quickly bleed opponents out with little risk to the wielder. This is further augmented by the weapon's &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Quickstep\"&gt;Quickstep&lt;/a&gt;, which allows the wielder to easily go in and out of hitting range, or outright dodge attacks that can be difficult to roll through, to build up status against opponents that are too aggressive to be comboed normally.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
{"id": "173172", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173172", "title": "Bandit (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Bandit is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%202\"&gt;Dark Souls 2&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt has high &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; and well above average &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;, meaning it lends itself rather well towards builds focused either on both or only the former (though it will have strong competition from the &lt;a href=\"Swordsman\"&gt;Swordsman&lt;/a&gt; when it comes to pure Dexterity builds). It is rather unsuitable to spells, even the &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Miracle&lt;/a&gt; ones, due to its extremely low &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. \nBandits are actually unable to speak to &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt; by default, the only class that can't do that, due to its extremely low Intelligence not meeting his minimum required amount of 3. \nThe starting weapons are somewhat mixed, with the &lt;a href=\"Short%20Bow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Short Bow&lt;/a&gt; following the higher starting value in Dexterity while the &lt;a href=\"Hand%20Axe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Hand Axe&lt;/a&gt; instead focuses on &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. The Hand Axe is most likely better replaced with an actually Dexterity-focused weapon, though those are in limited supply until &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Lenigrast\"&gt;Blacksmith Lenigrast's&lt;/a&gt; shop is opened, mostly the &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Things%20Betwixt\"&gt;Things Betwixt&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt;. Beyond extra weapons such as the &lt;a href=\"Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Rapier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Rapier&lt;/a&gt;, Lenigrast also holds the game's first infinite supply of ammunition (merely more &lt;a href=\"Wood%20Arrow\"&gt;Wood Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s, but still) and another Short Bow.\nUntil an unlimited source of arrows is acquired, they are best either saved for trying to pull individual enemies from groups or ambushes, or for trying to kill one of the early &lt;a href=\"Ogre\"&gt;Ogre&lt;/a&gt;s (either the one outside the Firekeeper's Hut in Things Betwixt at the start of the tutorial that also holds the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Ring\"&gt;Stone Ring&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Scholar of the First Sin&lt;/a&gt;-exclusive one on the way towards the Forest of Fallen Giants) for a large amount of extra &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Souls&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe class's &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Set\"&gt;Bandit Set&lt;/a&gt; is actually fairly good, as it has somewhat high physical defences and is, together with the &lt;a href=\"Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Knight's&lt;/a&gt; partial &lt;a href=\"Falconer%20Set\"&gt;Falconer Set&lt;/a&gt;, the only starting set with decent starting &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. \nDue to its very low &lt;a href=\"Adaptability\"&gt;Adaptability&lt;/a&gt; and Attunement it has a horrible roll (a mere 5 i-frames, compared to most other classes having 8 or 9 i-frames) and needs 5 points in Adaptability to improve this to 8 i-frames. \nThere is a curious disadvantage to its high &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;, higher than any other starting class: when using the &lt;a href=\"Third%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;Third Dragon Ring&lt;/a&gt;, it cannot receive the full benefit of the &lt;a href=\"Flynn%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Flynn's Ring&lt;/a&gt; and will get a light decrease of 4 Attack Rating compared to any other class. \nStarting Equipment.\nAs with all starting classes in Dark Souls 2, the &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; worn before the character creation can be found unequipped in the character's inventory. \nIt also starts with 10 &lt;a href=\"Lifegem\"&gt;Lifegem&lt;/a&gt;s as an equipped consumable. "}
