{"id": "54427", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54427", "title": "Bandit Axe", "text": "The Bandit Axe is an &lt;a href=\"Axes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nThe Bandit Axe possesses relatively high base damage and good strength scaling. Better than the standard &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Battle Axe&lt;/a&gt; due to its pure Strength scaling, which more than makes up for its slightly lower durability and higher weight, and makes it one of the most effective early Strength weapons. It is an excellent weapon, much like its later appearance as the Brigand Axe in \"Dark Souls III\", and can easily be used for the entire game with few-to-no issues, though one will probably also want a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Hammer&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt; for armored foes. "}
