{"id": "55964", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55964", "title": "Bandit Greataxe", "text": "The\u00a0Bandit Grataxe\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Bandit Greataxe is on a corpse in a pot located within &lt;a href=\"The%20Gutter\"&gt;The Gutter&lt;/a&gt;, right below the zip-line.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Bandit Greataxe is an unusual weapon, in that it has the statistics and moveset of a weapon that seems to fit into a category between standard &lt;a href=\"Axes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Axes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greataxes&lt;/a&gt;. In particular, it has a relatively fast one-handed moveset, consumes relatively little &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;, and\u00a0is the &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;lightest&lt;/a&gt; weapon in its class.\nIn spite of its faster and lighter moveset, it retains the standard 45 poise damage of its class, making it potent at stunlocking faster, armored, enemies, who may be able to attack quickly enough to retaliate against a slower weapon, or simply not &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; to a lighter weapon's attack.\nThe Bandit Greataxe has poor scaling and average base damage, meaning it is most effective when &lt;a href=\"Infusion\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt;. When fully upgraded and infused with an element, it will have a B scaling in the relevant stat, along with 259 base physical and elemental damage. Alternatively, a &lt;a href=\"Raw%20Stone\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt; infusion may be used to save a few levels in &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, at the cost of lower maximum damage potential.\nThe unorthodox traits of the weapon compounds with an extremely short reach and awkward two-handed moveset to create a uniquely unwieldy weapon in two-hands. When used in one-hand, however, it sports some distinct advantages that a player with the patience to learn the weapon's quirks may find to their liking.\nIt shares its moveset with the &lt;a href=\"Lion%20Greataxe\"&gt;Lion Greataxe&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Greataxe\"&gt;Black Dragon Greataxe&lt;/a&gt;, although the greater reach of these weapons makes the application of the moveset distinct to the Bandit Greataxe.\nGallery.\n&lt;a href=\"http%3A//youtu.be/BgEwPx84ViM\"&gt;Bandit Greataxe (complete showcase + dual wield and power stance)&lt;/a&gt;"}
