{"id": "90815", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=90815", "title": "Baneful Bird Ring", "text": "The Baneful Bird Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Old%20Iron%20King%20%28DLC%29\"&gt;Dark Souls II: Crown of the Old Iron King&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nAvailability.\nLocated on a corpse in &lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower\"&gt;Brume Tower&lt;/a&gt;, in view of the &lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower%23Bonfires\"&gt;Throne Floor&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. A lift must be taken to reach the ring, which in turn requires the player to find and use the &lt;a href=\"Scorching%20Iron%20Scepter\"&gt;Scorching Iron Scepter&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nIncreases the stability of all equipped items by 5, thereby reducing the stamina damage taken when blocking. The ring is particularly powerful when combined with a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, as the already low stamina damage taken can be reduced by a larger fraction, allowing players to easily weather repeated hits."}
{"id": "12429", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12429", "title": "Banshee", "text": "Banshee is a type of &lt;a href=\"Enemies\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nThere are only two that can be found in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"New%20Londo%20Ruins\"&gt;New Londo Ruins&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThey scream when the player gets too close, and is said to attract other &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt;s. The main differences between Banshees and Ghosts are their red, glowing eyes, the &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Blade\"&gt;Ghost Blade&lt;/a&gt; half-held in one hand, and the baby they carry.\u00a0\nCurse.\nLike the Ghost, the Banshee can only be killed if the player is &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Cursed&lt;/a&gt;, or is carrying a cursed weapon. &lt;a href=\"Transient%20Curse\"&gt;Transient Curse&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0allows temporary contact with a Banshee without actually being cursed. This is considered a &lt;a href=\"self%20augmentation\"&gt;self augmentation&lt;/a&gt; effect, and thus prevents the use of other self augmentations.\nIf the player is not cursed, they will not be able to interact with the Banshee in any way. This includes damaging it, of course, but also blocking it, or just reducing the damage taken with armor. Furthermore, the Banshee's attacks will always stagger the player when not cursed, as it bypasses armor, leaving the player &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;poiseless&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlayers can also use cursed weapons (such as the &lt;a href=\"Jagged%20Ghost%20Blade\"&gt;Jagged Ghost Blade&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20of%20Artorias%20%28Cursed%29\"&gt;Cursed Greatsword of Artorias&lt;/a&gt;). While this allows striking the Banshee, it will still leave the player unable to block with a &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, or reduce damage taken with armor. Cursed weapons can also be held with two hands to block.\nIf possible, the most complete strategy is to use a Transient Curse, but still wield a cursed weapon. This makes it so that the player is not left completely defenseless should the Transient Curse end at a bad time, or without the player noticing."}
{"id": "47527", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47527", "title": "Barbed Club", "text": "The Barbed Club\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAcquired by trading the &lt;a href=\"Flexile%20Sentry%20Soul\"&gt;Flexile Sentry Soul&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt; along with 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nEarly game, this weapon will fall short due to its high stat requirements, scaling, and the necessity to obtain a rare upgrade material to make it stronger. It only shines later, when a character has very high Strength and Dexterity.\nStill, ironically, by the time it starts becoming good, the player may rather obtain the superior &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Warpick\"&gt;Black Dragon Warpick&lt;/a&gt;, which upgrades using the same materials. Despite lacking bleed, it has higher durability and requires far lower stats to reach the same damage when infused.\nMoveset.\nIts &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; is the same as all the other medium hammers, e.g. &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Star%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Morning Star&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Reinforced%20Club%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Reinforced Club&lt;/a&gt;, and so on."}
