{"id": "125917", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=125917", "title": "Bashful Ray", "text": "Bashful Ray is a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;summon&lt;/a&gt; found in .\nDescription.\nHe dons the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Shadow Set&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Prisoner%27s%20Hood\"&gt;Prisoner's Hood&lt;/a&gt; and is equipped with the &lt;a href=\"Simpleton%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Simpleton's Ring&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Slumbering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;. He mostly fights by either &lt;a href=\"dualwield\"&gt;dualwield&lt;/a&gt;ing a pair of &lt;a href=\"Umbral%20Dagger\"&gt;Umbral Dagger&lt;/a&gt;s or a pair of &lt;a href=\"Claws%20%28weapon%29\"&gt;Claws&lt;/a&gt;. He often resorts to cast with his &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; when surrounded or against a strong &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;. When not in combat, he'll search his surroundings with the help of &lt;a href=\"Binoculars%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Binoculars&lt;/a&gt;. He can also use &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus&lt;/a&gt; to replenish his &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nDespite his raggedy appearance, Ray has a lot of &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; and can easily tank whatever is thrown at him. Regardless of this, he's also skilled at dodging and can heal himself up to a maximum of ten times.\nThe quick combos he can dish out with his dual weapons will be deadly for most enemies, as they'll end up stunlocked.\nRay's arsenal of &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; includes &lt;a href=\"Combustion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Combustion&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Flame\"&gt;Lingering Flame&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Firestorm%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Firestorm&lt;/a&gt;. The latter two in particular are perfect to help the player and himself get out of a situation where they're being overwhelmed by an assault of numerous mobs. Albeit rarely, he may also cast &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Orb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire Orb&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Great%20Fireball%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Fireball&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn rare occasions, he'll attempt to aggro distant enemies with &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Throwing Knifes&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile he possesses high resistance to &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, he's susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Petrification\"&gt;Petrification&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe fact that he's mostly available as a &lt;a href=\"shade\"&gt;shade&lt;/a&gt; can be a double-edged sword: while this means that the player can only reap the benefit of his cooperation for a short period of time, Ray can be used to clean up areas where the boss is already dead to help with strong enemies or &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;invaders&lt;/a&gt;, or can be brought to another nearby boss.\nLocations.\nHe may be summoned at the following locations:\nHis summon sign is found in the cell with the corpse holding a &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Star%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Morning Star&lt;/a&gt;. He can be summoned for both the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Lords\"&gt;Skeleton Lords&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Executioner%27s%20Chariot\"&gt;Executioner's Chariot&lt;/a&gt;. His health is 6,900, and 10,074 in NG+\nHis summon sign is placed in front of the wooden rails that block the path to &lt;a href=\"Laddersmith%20Gilligan\"&gt;Gilligan&lt;/a&gt;.\nHis summon sign is located between the two &lt;a href=\"Razorback%20Nightcrawler\"&gt;Razorback Nightcrawler&lt;/a&gt;s.\nHis summon sign is found inside the room next to &lt;a href=\"Ornifex\"&gt;Ornifex&lt;/a&gt;'s house, past the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Crystal%20Lizard\"&gt;Red Crystal Lizard&lt;/a&gt;.\nHis summon sign will appear near one of the torch wielding golem, only if the torches of both golems have been lit. He can assist the player against the &lt;a href=\"Dragonrider\"&gt;Dragonrider&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Throne%20Watcher%20and%20Throne%20Defender\"&gt;Throne Watcher and Throne Defender&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nashandra\"&gt;Nashandra&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aldia\"&gt;Aldia&lt;/a&gt;. Furthermore, he can help against the two &lt;a href=\"Pursuers\"&gt;Pursuers&lt;/a&gt; that spawn in the throne room at &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Intensity\"&gt;Bonfire Intensity&lt;/a&gt; 2+.\nHis summon sign is placed in the area with a wooden chest containing a &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Slab%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Titanite Slab&lt;/a&gt; (that used to be a &lt;a href=\"Mimic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;base game&lt;/a&gt;) before the &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Warpick\"&gt;Warpick&lt;/a&gt; wielding &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper\"&gt;Drakekeeper&lt;/a&gt; that guards the door to the metal chest containing the &lt;a href=\"Third%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;Third Dragon Ring&lt;/a&gt;. Note that summoning any &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt; will turn all the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt;s hostile.\nDefenses.\n&lt;tabber&gt; General =\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "4690", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4690", "title": "Basilisk", "text": "The Basilisk is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nBasilisks are found initially in the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt;, then again in &lt;a href=\"The%20Great%20Hollow\"&gt;The Great Hollow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ash%20Lake\"&gt;Ash Lake&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nBasilisks are slender, scrawny lizards. Upon seeing the player, it will frantically scramble or leap into position and exhale a grey mist that will quickly overwhelm the player with the &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; status, causing immediate death.\nThe bulbous appendages that appear on the basilisk are not its actual eyes. The basilisk's true eyes are the small yellow beads that appear right over its mouth.\nGeneral Information.\nThe basilisk can only cause curse status; they cause no other effects or any direct damage in any form unless they jump directly on the player.\nThe basilisks in the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt; guard the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Evil%20Eye\"&gt;Ring of the Evil Eye&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nBasilisks have low health and no &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;, making them easy to kill with almost any attack. Their most dangerous move is the leaping curse breath attack, due to its low wind-up, while their standing curse breath is far more telegraphed and easily interrupted. With sufficient curse resistance and rapid offense even groups of basilisks won't prove too challenging as long as the player is mindful of the clouds.\nBasilisks are deaf, meaning they struggle to detect the player unless they see or touch them. Even if they do detect the player, they are slow to turn around, often favoring simply running away before turning around, meaning that they struggle to react to the player getting behind them.\nCritical.\nHitting any part of a basilisk's face will deal increased damage. Because the face is the point that gets targeted when locking onto the basilisk, using &lt;a href=\"thrust\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; attacks will work exceedingly well against basilisks, as each strike will almost guarantee this bonus damage.\nMelee.\nBasilisks\u00a0have no melee attacks whatsoever. \u00a0Combined with relatively low health, they can be quickly dealt with. However getting\u00a0too close risks exposure to Curse and is ill-advised if they are in any significant numbers, or the player has low Curse resistance.\nConsidering their only means of offense are their Curse attacks, the player could equip a shield\u00a0with high Curse block in order to take basilisks down more easily. &lt;a href=\"Spears\"&gt;Spears&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords\"&gt;Thrusting Swords&lt;/a&gt; are excellent for this strategy, as they can strike from behind shields.\nRanged.\nBasilisks stagger from just about any hit, and can easily be pelted with arrows without them being able to execute a single attack. This gives the added bonus of allowing players to pull one or two basilisks at a time, rather than have the entire swarm of seven or so rushing after them."}
{"id": "62149", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=62149", "title": "Basilisk (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Basilisk is an found in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\n&lt;a href=\"Shaded%20Woods\"&gt;Shaded Woods&lt;/a&gt;: One is encountered directly behind the door to the entrance of the area. Several more can be found near the final bonfire if the player falls through either of two pit traps into their lair. A large, more powerful variant can be found approximately halfway between the Shaded Woods bonfire and the fog gate to &lt;a href=\"Scorpioness%20Najka\"&gt;Scorpioness Najka&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove Tseldora&lt;/a&gt;: There are several hiding in the sand near the final bonfire.\n&lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;: They can be found inside the carriages. To break them loose, an &lt;a href=\"Ogre\"&gt;Ogre&lt;/a&gt; must destroy the carriage. A &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Basilisk\"&gt;Giant Basilisk&lt;/a&gt; is also found inside a cage.\nIn \"\", one Basilisk is found in the area between\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Heide%27s%20Tower%20of%20Flame\"&gt;Heide's Tower of Flame&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"No-man%27s%20Wharf\"&gt;No-man's Wharf&lt;/a&gt;. Several are also encountered in &lt;a href=\"Things%20Betwixt\"&gt;Things-Betwixt&lt;/a&gt;, on the path leading to the two Ogres on the beach. Several more can be found at &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Amana\"&gt;Shrine of Amana&lt;/a&gt;, one at the end of a side path shortly after the first bonfire, and a few more between the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20of%20Song\"&gt;Demon of Song&lt;/a&gt; and the final bonfire.\nAttacks.\nA Basilisk's most dangerous ability is to &lt;a href=\"Petrification\"&gt;Petrify&lt;/a&gt; the player, causing instant death. Basilisks can also perform a series of melee attacks such as claw swipes, tail slashes and leaping headbutts, all of which are surprisingly potent due to their agility. The addition of melee attacks makes them significantly more dangerous than their &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;counterparts&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nStrategy.\nRanged attacks are generally the safest way to dispatch Basilisks, as they are unable to attack anything outside of melee range. Care should be taken, however, as they may end up cornering the player and making them unable to escape the &lt;a href=\"Petrification\"&gt;Petrification&lt;/a&gt; mist. Planning an escape route before engaging a group of Basilisks is advisable.\nBasilisks have little to no &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. This means that they can be stun-locked by almost any attack. Using wide-swinging weapons, like a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, will allow the player to deal with larger groups of Basilisks with relative ease.\nThey have very little health, even at higher levels of &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt;, which means that if they are isolated, players can simply wait for them to discharge their petrifying mist and then flank it.\nBeing a beast, Basilisks have a weakness to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. As such, &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; and flame infused or buffed weapons will deal considerable damage."}
{"id": "137584", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137584", "title": "Basilisk (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Basilisks are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nBasilisks are slim lizards with a large head and seemingly large eyes. Upon sensing the player, the basilisk will charge them before leaping in the air to either spew a gray mist that inflicts &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;curse&lt;/a&gt; or leaping behind the player in an attempt to block off an escape route. They move quickly in a forward direction but turn slowly.\nThe bulbous appendages that appear on the basilisk are not its actual eyes. The basilisks eyes are the small yellow beads that appear right over its mouth.\nBasilisks are often found guarding something; the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Scroll\"&gt;Golden Scroll&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Clutch%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark Clutch Ring&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Cell%20Key\"&gt;Old Cell Key&lt;/a&gt;, and just before &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Slayer%20Tsorig\"&gt;Tsorig&lt;/a&gt;'s encounter.\nLocations.\nBasilisks are found in the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, near the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Scroll\"&gt;Golden Scroll&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Antiquated%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Antiquated Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nFurther into the game, the player will find a sewer in the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; with two chests, one being a &lt;a href=\"Mimic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt;; the normal chest contains the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Cell%20Key\"&gt;Old Cell Key&lt;/a&gt;. After obtaining the item, the player will be ambushed by several basilisks.\nThe final place that basilisks reside in is down in the lower levels of &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;, just before being attacked by &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Slayer%20Tsorig\"&gt;Knight Slayer Tsorig&lt;/a&gt; near a large pool of lava.\nStrategy.\nBasilisks are very slippery foes that can be hard to kill due to their evasiveness. Because they only possess breath attacks, they are incapable of damaging the player in any way short of inflicting the status effect.\nIdeally, Basilisks should be engaged in a situation where the player has mobility options. Simply attack and kill a Basilisk while attempting to stay outside of the mist, and retreat as needed if Curse buildup becomes too high. Large weapons with high impact and stagger can lock down Basilisks long enough to finish them off. While weapons with horizontal sweep can allow the player to hit multiple targets at once, vertically attacking weapons can sometimes knock them out of the air as they perform pouncing attacks or jumping retreats.\nAs they are rarely encountered in situations where they are mixed alongside other enemy types, it is best to be patient and slowly but methodically clear out Basilisk nests before moving on. So long as attention is paid to Curse buildup and no additional enemies join the fray, Basilisks can be safely dispatched."}
{"id": "131079", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131079", "title": "Basin of Vows", "text": "The Basin of Vows is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nApproaching the beheading statue behind Emma's chair with the Basin of Vows in hand will trigger the &lt;a href=\"Dancer%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Dancer of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt; fight.\nOnce the Dancer has been defeated, interacting with the beheading statue will place the basin in front of it, triggering a cutscene that unlocks access to &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Castle\"&gt;Lothric Castle&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5094", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5094", "title": "Bastard Sword", "text": "The Bastard Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Bastard Sword may be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Andre%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Andre of Astora&lt;/a&gt; for 3,000 &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nBastard Sword is one of the few true Quality Scaling weapons at 51% &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and 51% &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; scaling. This makes it a good choice for players opting for a 27 Str 40 Dex Quality Build. This weapon will deal slightly more damage than &lt;a href=\"Claymore\"&gt;Claymore&lt;/a&gt; at the same stat investment, but has shorter reach. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "34025", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34025", "title": "Bastard Sword (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Bastard Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Bastard Sword is a fairly strong &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; that is available near the start of the player's journey.\nThe low stat requirement and ease of access generally gives the Bastard Sword the role of an early-game weapon that is only used until it can be switched for a stronger weapon. Despite this, it can still hold its own in the late-game due to its relatively high base damage. This is especially true of characters that use spell buffs as the damage buffs provide is determined mainly by the base AR of the weapon and affinity with infusions.\nIt has the same moveset as the Claymore, save for the strong attacks, which are overhead swings instead of thrusts. The fast attacks combine with the high &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; break to allow the weapon to stagger most enemies, including &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; opponents, with ease.\nAlthough the &lt;a href=\"Claymore%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Claymore&lt;/a&gt; may be considered better, the Bastard Sword's only true weakness is the absence of any easy-to-use thrust, being limited to the rolling attack."}
{"id": "130279", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130279", "title": "Bastard Sword (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Bastard Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nA ubiquitous weapon, the Bastard Sword is a very economical greatsword that makes it strong on a number of builds.\nAt 8.0 units, the Bastard Sword is the third-lightest greatsword in the game, beat by the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wolnir%27s%20Holy%20Sword\"&gt;Wolnir's Holy Sword&lt;/a&gt; and tying with the &lt;a href=\"Storm%20Ruler\"&gt;Storm Ruler&lt;/a&gt;. As well, it has virtually no &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; requirements to wield, allowing almost any build to equip and use it. And finally, its &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; consumption is among the lowest among all greatswords in the game, granting its wielder improved stamina economy.\nThe Bastard Sword specializes in horizontal and vertical slashing attacks. It has a similar moveset to the &lt;a href=\"Claymore%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Claymore&lt;/a&gt;, though it lacks the latter's thrusting attacks, which limits its reach and makes it difficult to use in corridors.\nOn physical builds, the Bastard Sword possesses high &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; scaling, allowing it to deal high potential damage when two-handed. It is also one of only two greatswords with the &lt;a href=\"Stomp\"&gt;Stomp&lt;/a&gt; weapon art, and the only one with the &lt;a href=\"Stomp%20%28upward%29\"&gt;upward slash&lt;/a&gt; variant (the other, the &lt;a href=\"Executioner%27s%20Greatsword\"&gt;Executioner's Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, has the &lt;a href=\"Stomp%20%28spin%29\"&gt;horizontal spinning slash&lt;/a&gt;), allowing it to be used to win trades against other players who are using similar-sized or even larger weapons. For these two reasons, the Bastard Sword can be quite powerful in the right hands with a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Gem\"&gt;Heavy&lt;/a&gt; infusion and high amounts of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard ."}
{"id": "172716", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=172716", "title": "Bastard Sword Dark Spirit", "text": "Bastard Sword Dark Spirit is an &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; that appears in the &lt;a href=\"Things%20Betwixt\"&gt;Things Betwixt&lt;/a&gt; only after all the braziers in the area are lit.\nDescription.\nThis &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;Dark Spirit&lt;/a&gt; dons the full &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; and is armed with a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nHer deceptively tattered appearance hides a fearsome &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;Dark Spirit&lt;/a&gt; that takes full advantage of the wide swings of her &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; and the narrow path where she's encountered. It's recommended to fight her inside one of the tree, even just to avoid pushing her down a chasm and losing the &lt;a href=\"Petrified%20Something\"&gt;drop&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlayers can exploit her lack of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; and ranged attacks to stunlocked her from a safe distance.\nEven low &lt;a href=\"Level%20Up%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;level&lt;/a&gt; players can easily dispatch this enemy with the &lt;a href=\"Critical%20attack\"&gt;critical attacks&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; that's found in the area.\nLocation.\nShe will spawn underneath &lt;a href=\"Dyna%20%26amp%3B%20Tillo\"&gt;Dyna &amp; Tillo&lt;/a&gt;'s nest, once all the braziers of the area have been lit."}
{"id": "56502", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56502", "title": "Bastille Key", "text": "The Bastille Key is a &lt;a href=\"Key%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nFound on a corpse in the area beyond the &lt;a href=\"Belfry%20Gargoyles\"&gt;Belfry Gargoyles&lt;/a&gt;. Next to the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; is a ladder which leads down to a small area with seven &lt;a href=\"Stray%20Hound\"&gt;Stray Hound&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Vorgel%20the%20Sinner\"&gt;Vorgel the Sinner&lt;/a&gt; and some minor loot.\n\"Scholar of the First Sin\".\nFound on a corpse hidden behind some breakable debris directly to the left after leaving the &lt;a href=\"Servants%27%20Quarters\"&gt;Servants' Quarters&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "60772", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=60772", "title": "Bat Staff", "text": "The Bat Staff is a &lt;a href=\"Staves\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Mage\"&gt;Hollow Mage&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove Tseldora&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nPrior to &lt;a href=\"patch%201.06\"&gt;patch 1.06&lt;/a&gt;, the Bat Staff could inflict extra &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; on an enemy when casting &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fog%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark Fog&lt;/a&gt;, in addition to when striking enemies with the staff. However, after patch 1.06, the Bat Staff only inflicts poison build-up when attacking an opponent directly.\nIn terms of casting ability, the Bat Staff is superior to the &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Sorcerer's Staff&lt;/a&gt; in terms of both spell bonuses and &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;; however, it has slightly less &lt;a href=\"casting%20speed\"&gt;casting speed&lt;/a&gt; and requires more &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; to use. If the player is a &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;hex&lt;/a&gt; user, however, the Bat Staff is quickly outclassed by the &lt;a href=\"Archdrake%20Staff\"&gt;Archdrake Staff&lt;/a&gt;, which can be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Felkin%20the%20Outcast\"&gt;Felkin the Outcast&lt;/a&gt; earlier than when a &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; may drop the Bat Staff (so long as the player has an effective &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; value of 8)."}
