{"id": "2467", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2467", "title": "Battle Axe", "text": "The Battle Axe is an &lt;a href=\"Axes\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nHas a decent starting damage compared to some other\u00a0axes\u00a0in the game, and it remains a reasonably powerful weapon for the entire game. However, its disadvantage lies in its quite short range, making it necessary to get close to enemies to hit them.\nLike all &lt;a href=\"Axes\"&gt;Axes&lt;/a&gt;, if an attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal. This makes this weapon capable of gaining &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Sweet_Spot_Damage_Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot Damage&lt;/a&gt; bonus. \nDue its high damage and ability to be purchased multiple times, it is a popular choice for SL1 (Soul Level 1) playthroughs when upgraded along such as &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;. If using this weapon for a SL1 run refer to this Loadouts Chart for which Upgrade Path or Resin will be best for each boss. Though it deals less damage compared to &lt;a href=\"Reinforced%20Club\"&gt;Reinforced Club&lt;/a&gt; for SL1, it is still a popular choice due to its faster recovery speed. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "54429", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54429", "title": "Battle Axe (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Battle Axe is an &lt;a href=\"Axes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nThe Battle Axe is outright weaker than the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Axe\"&gt;Bandit Axe&lt;/a&gt;, with inferior scaling that requires massive Dexterity to even get close to matching the Bandit Axe's power. This weakness extends to when the weapon is infused. Despite its slightly higher durability, in most cases, players are best simply using this weapon until they reach &lt;a href=\"No-man%27s%20Wharf\"&gt;No-man's Wharf&lt;/a&gt; and can obtain its better counterpart, if they use it at all. After all, with more hits necessary to down an enemy, durability will be used up faster regardless."}
{"id": "132898", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132898", "title": "Battle Axe (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Battle Axe is an &lt;a href=\"Axes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nDoes not rebound off shields when two-handed. Respectable damage and poise reduction as a standard axe.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
{"id": "19755", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19755", "title": "Battle of Stoicism", "text": "The is an online &lt;a href=\"gameplay\"&gt;gameplay&lt;/a&gt; function in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nThe entrances to the Battle of Stoicism arenas are found in the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20of%20Stoicism%20Gazebo\"&gt;Battle of Stoicism Gazebo&lt;/a&gt;, just before the &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Township\"&gt;Oolacile Township&lt;/a&gt;. Down the right-hand side of the passage that leads there.\nTypes of matches.\nDuels.\nIn this mode, two players are chosen to fight each other in an arena. The winner takes a prize.\nTeam.\nSimilar to Duel mode, in this one, four players are divided into two teams and must defeat the enemy team, the winning team takes the prize.\nDeathmatch.\nIn this one, four players must battle against each other, and every player killed grants prizes to all other players alive, the last one standing wins.\nRules and overall mechanics.\nRules.\nThere are a set of rules that are applied to all the three modes of the , listed below:\nMechanics.\nAfter the player chooses a game mode, they are transported to the lobby, in which orange signs with the rules of the game are spread throughout the place. To enter a battle, the player must stand on one of the trap doors available to begin the game.\nThere are two types of trap doors, the hosting trap door, and the common trap door. The hosting trap door turns the player standing on it a host, inviting other players that are standing on the common trap doors. More common trap doors become available depending on the mode chosen, each leading to an arena with other players. The players take no damage when the trap door opens.\nIf the player decides to leave the lobby, there is a special bonfire that teleports them back to the gazebo.\nTrivia.\nEven though the is completely focused on &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, with rules made to guarantee a fair duel, it is not a very popular area for PvP, probably because of the lack of reward when a player wins a match.\nMusic.\n&lt;embedvideo service=\"youtube\" alignment=\"center\" description=\"Dark Souls \u2014 Battle of Stoicism by \"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NwK0SRie1wU&lt;/embedvideo&gt;"}
{"id": "23994", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23994", "title": "Battle of Stoicism Gazebo", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"location\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", available only in the \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\"\u00a0DLC.\nLocation.\nIt is located right before the &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Township\"&gt;Oolacile Township&lt;/a&gt;, after the battle with &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Artorias\"&gt;Knight Artorias&lt;/a&gt;. It is a small corridor to the right of the path that leads to the township.\nDescription.\nThe is a very small area that serves only for players to get into the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20of%20Stoicism\"&gt;Battle of Stoicism&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "13205", "revid": "37406887", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13205", "title": "Batwing Demon", "text": "Batwing Demons are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nThey are seen for the first time in &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt; but are encountered as enemies throughout &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nBatwing Demons are winged, imp-like creatures with tall hind legs and long arms. They wield the &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Spear\"&gt;Demon's Spear&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0a &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Damage%20Type%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; based weapon, and have long tails that appear to have no use aside from balancing their body during flight.\nNotes.\nBatwing Demons are the means of transportation, similar to the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Crow\"&gt;Giant Crow&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0between the end of &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt; and the beginning of &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;. From Sen's Fortress, after defeating the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt;, interaction with the gold &lt;a href=\"Resonance%20Ring\"&gt;resonance ring&lt;/a&gt; that appears will prompt several demons to carry the player by the arms to the outer wall of Anor Londo. To return to Sen's Fortress from Anor Londo, one must \"talk\" to a lone demon perched on a merlon."}
