{"id": "61884", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=61884", "title": "Bell Keeper Shield", "text": "The Bell Keeper Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nCharacteristics.\nWith average &lt;a href=\"physical%20defense\"&gt;physical defense&lt;/a&gt; and poor &lt;a href=\"elemental%20defense\"&gt;elemental defense&lt;/a&gt;s, the Bell Keeper Shield is unremarkable for the most part. The exception is its excellent &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29%23Magic%20Defense\"&gt;magic defense&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stability\"&gt;Stability&lt;/a&gt; coupled with its low &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement, which makes it a solid choice for any player when magic damage is an issue.\nIt is inferior to the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shield%20%28Shield%29\"&gt;Magic Shield&lt;/a&gt; in terms of direct damage reduction, and is arguably harder to get. However, it has marginally better protection against &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt; and ties with the highest Stability among the &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Small Shields&lt;/a&gt;."}
