{"id": "11697", "revid": "357070", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11697", "title": "Berenike Knight", "text": " \nBerenike Knights, also known as Heavy Knights,\u00a0are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\u00a0\nDescription.\nLarge and clad in the &lt;a href=\"Steel%20Set\"&gt;Steel Set&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0they wield either a large &lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Greatsword\"&gt;Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, depending on the location where they are found, along with a &lt;a href=\"Tower%20Shield\"&gt;Tower Shield&lt;/a&gt;. All Berenike Knights can be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;, but cannot be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;riposted&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nBerenike Knights were known for their &lt;a href=\"Steel%20Set\"&gt;heavy armor of steel&lt;/a&gt; and used ultra heavy &lt;a href=\"Tower%20Shield\"&gt;Tower Shield&lt;/a&gt;s forged with thick plates of iron, favoring hard defense and stability, and gigantic swords capable of causing monstrous damage and for their immense strength they were extolled as the mightiest of mighty. Among them, &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Tarkus\"&gt;Black Iron Tarkus&lt;/a&gt; was renowned even among his fellow knights for his great strength and he wore an &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Set\"&gt;ultra heavy armor&lt;/a&gt; made of special black iron so heavy that only he was able to wear it but that provided him with a strong defense against fire and his &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Greatshield\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, made of the same material, was even heavier than that of his fellow knights.\nHowever as the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; started to fade countless among the ranks of the &lt;a href=\"Berenike%20Knight\"&gt;Berenike Knight&lt;/a&gt;s became Undead and ventured to &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt;. Here they tried to make their way toward Anor Londo, through the only possible access: &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;. The knights of Berenike and Tarkus thus entered the dangerous proving ground but for naught as through decades of failure they were not able to advance and ended up as &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;s, becoming a threat to all the other Undead in the location. After a grueling and long battle, few of them eventually managed to reach the end of the path of Sen's Fortress and challenge the last trial in the form of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt;. The mighty Tarkus managed to defeat even the guardian of Anor Londo, thus gaining access to the city of the gods. Despite his immense strength, once he reached Anor Londo, Tarkus perished at the hands of the &lt;a href=\"Painting%20Guardian\"&gt;Painting Guardian&lt;/a&gt;s before he could reach \"&lt;a href=\"Gwynevere%2C%20Princess%20of%20Sunlight\"&gt;Gwynevere, Princess of Sunlight&lt;/a&gt;\" and obtain the &lt;a href=\"Lordvessel\"&gt;Lordvessel&lt;/a&gt; and the few Berenite Knights that followed him ended up trapped inside the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;.\nEnemy Information.\nAttacks.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nMace=\nSword=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "49755", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49755", "title": "Berserker Blade", "text": "The\u00a0Berserker Blade is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Katanas%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;katana&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Berserker Blade can be found in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Belfry%20Sol\"&gt;Belfry Sol&lt;/a&gt;. It is dropped by the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Mad%20Warrior\"&gt;Mad Warrior&lt;/a&gt; that uncommonly spawns (resting at a bonfire a few times should cause it to respawn). However, acquiring the Berserker Blade also requires that the player be a member of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bell%20Keepers\"&gt;Bell Keepers&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0covenant, as the phantom will not spawn unless the player is in the covenant. Note that the Mad Warrior will spawn less frequently the more he is killed.\nAlternatively, it can be dropped by the &lt;a href=\"Prowlers\"&gt;Prowlers&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower\"&gt;Brume Tower&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Bersker Blade is one of the highest damage katanas available, and it features a standard moveset revolving around vertical slashes and delayed strong attacks. Its main drawbacks compared to other katanas are its short length, and the time-consuming way it is obtained.\nBeing a rare drop from the Mad Warrior and Prowlers; the process of even getting this weapon can be arduous, but its excellent scaling in &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; allows it to compete with the &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Blade%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Chaos Blade&lt;/a&gt;. Compared to the Chaos Blade, it also comes with the advantages of not draining the wielder's health points and being more easily accessible, though likely slower to obtain, due to the nature of random drops."}
{"id": "90537", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=90537", "title": "Bewitched Alonne Sword", "text": "The Bewitched Alonne Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Katanas%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;katana&lt;/a&gt; in .\nAvailability.\nThe Bewitched Alonne Sword is obtained by giving the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Sir%20Alonne\"&gt;Soul of Sir Alonne&lt;/a&gt;, along with 18,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Souls&lt;/a&gt;, to &lt;a href=\"Weaponsmith%20Ornifex\"&gt;Weaponsmith Ornifex&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Bewitched Alonne Sword should be treated with similar thought as &lt;a href=\"Santier%27s%20Spear\"&gt;Santier's Spear&lt;/a&gt; as it combines several attacks from other &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Types%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon classes&lt;/a&gt; into its &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;. Its one-handed light attack, its two-handed &lt;a href=\"rolling\"&gt;rolling&lt;/a&gt; and standing light attacks are not what one might expect from a katana. They are borrowed from the &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt; classes.\nIt uses the Straight Sword moveset when &lt;a href=\"Power%20Stance\"&gt;Power Stance&lt;/a&gt;d.\nIt's the weakest of the katanas, but has the second highest &lt;a href=\"reach\"&gt;reach&lt;/a&gt; among them, which meshes well with the weapon's wide swings. Its &lt;a href=\"critical\"&gt;critical&lt;/a&gt; modifier is very low in comparison to similar weapons, and it is fully buffable.\nSpecial ability.\nRather than a &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt;, the Bewitched Alonne Sword possesses a damage increasing buff. When held in two hands and the \"parry\" button is pressed the player will stab themself, taking damage, which can be reduced by high &lt;a href=\"physical%20defence\"&gt;physical defence&lt;/a&gt;, while buffing the weapon for around 30 seconds after the player pulls the sword out of their body. The buff increases its Scaling AR by 60% for the duration of the buff, including the &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; of the weapon.\nWhen activating the buff, the blade will release a harmful aura which, similarly to &lt;a href=\"Wrath%20of%20the%20Gods%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Wrath of the Gods&lt;/a&gt;, damages and &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt;s any enemies close to the player."}
{"id": "8038", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8038", "title": "Big Hat", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Big Hat is a &lt;a href=\"head%20armor\"&gt;head armor&lt;/a&gt; piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of &lt;a href=\"Big%20Hat%27s%20Set\"&gt;Big Hat's Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Big%20Hat%20Logan\"&gt;Big Hat Logan&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0when killed in &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nOffers the highest &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; defenses of any &lt;a href=\"headpiece\"&gt;headpiece&lt;/a&gt; in the game, as well as decent &lt;a href=\"Physical%20defense\"&gt;Physical defense&lt;/a&gt;s for its &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;. However, it has very low &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Defense\"&gt;Fire Defense&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen fully upgraded, its Magic Defense is extraordinarily high; at 66.7 it is, by far, unmatched by any headpiece.\nUpgrades.\nRequires 200 &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; per upgrade.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "7616", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7616", "title": "Big Hat's Set", "text": "Big Hat's Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nPlot.\nBig Hat's Set is hinted to be nothing more than unkempt, worn out sorcerer's apprentice robes. Big Hat Logan used his abnormally large hat to block out stares from passersby so that he could concentrate on his thoughts. At the end of his lucidity during his studies in the Duke's Archives, Big Hat Logan discarded his set in his attempts to become more like his idol, &lt;a href=\"Seath%20the%20Scaleless\"&gt;Seath the Scaleless&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Big Hat offers the highest &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; resistance of any headgear in the game, as well as being relatively light. The rest of the set is fairly typical for a light set, with low weight at the cost of low defenses in general and no &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nDespite having identical names in-game, the Traveling Gloves in Big Hat's set is aesthetically and statistically different from the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Traveling%20Gloves%20%28Holy%20Set%29\"&gt;Traveling Gloves&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Set\"&gt;Holy Set&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "2419", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2419", "title": "Big Hat Logan", "text": "Big Hat Logan (\u30d3\u30c3\u30b0\u30cf\u30c3\u30c8 \u30ed\u30fc\u30ac\u30f3 \"Biggu Hatto Ro-gan\"), seeker of knowledge, is mentor to &lt;a href=\"Griggs%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Griggs of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; and an advanced &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; trainer in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". He is voiced by .\nPlot.\nBig Hat Logan is first encountered in &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;. His cage is hidden behind a wall, which can be destroyed by manipulating the iron ball trap mechanism, using a powerful enough weapon, or goading the sleeping man-serpent guard to attack the wall. After freeing him with either the &lt;a href=\"Cage%20Key\"&gt;Cage Key&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Master%20Key\"&gt;Master Key&lt;/a&gt;, Big Hat Logan thanks the player and later retreats to &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;. There, he accompanies &lt;a href=\"Griggs%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Griggs of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; and offers to sell the player advanced &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt;.\nBig Hat Logan soon leaves Firelink Shrine after the &lt;a href=\"Lordvessel\"&gt;Lordvessel&lt;/a&gt; has been obtained. He is then jailed in &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt;. Logan explains that he is there to study &lt;a href=\"Seath%20the%20Scaleless\"&gt;Seath the Scaleless&lt;/a&gt; and his magic. After freeing him with the &lt;a href=\"Archive%20Tower%20Giant%20Cell%20Key\"&gt;Archive Tower Giant Cell Key&lt;/a&gt;, players can find Logan in an ancillary library close to the third bonfire in The Duke's Archives, where he sells Crystal Sorceries as well as his prior spells. Alternatively, if not freed by you by Seath's defeat, he will free himself and move to the library.\nUnfortunately, Logan's infatuation with Seath's magic eventually drives him insane after Seath has been defeated and his entire stock of spells has been purchased. Speaking with him again, after the above conditions are met, will cause him to move to the large chamber where Seath the Scaleless was first encountered and become hostile.\nLore.\nMaster Logan was a famous &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; and a royal member of the &lt;a href=\"Vinheim\"&gt;Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; Dragon School before he turned Undead about one hundred years ago. His nickname stems from the gigantic hat he wore which completely hid his face; he used it to block the noise and stares from those around him in order to focus his thoughts. His &lt;a href=\"Logan%27s%20Catalyst\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; was once an ordinary &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%27s%20Catalyst\"&gt;catalyst&lt;/a&gt; employed by the Sorcerers of Vinheim, but it has since been strengthened due to lengthy use over time. Similarly, his &lt;a href=\"Sage%20Robe\"&gt;robe&lt;/a&gt; is one typically worn by apprentices at Dragon School.\nLogan is credited with having developed the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt; Sorcery, among others, which is referenced repeatedly in the legends and is said to be on par with &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lord Gwyn's&lt;/a&gt; lightning.\nIn his attempt to reach &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, presumably to gain access to &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt; and its vast store of endless knowledge, he became imprisoned in &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;, where he first encounters the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nBig Hat Logan has a repertoire of dangerous Sorceries, including &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Soulmass\"&gt;Homing Soulmass&lt;/a&gt;. If attacked later in the game, he also possesses their augmented crystal variants. However, he is fairly fragile and can be killed before he deals too much damage.\nIf killed when encountered in Sen's Fortress or Firelink Shrine, he will not drop anything.\nWares.\nLogan will not sell anything to the player unless they have at least 15 Intelligence.\nCharacter Information.\nEquipment.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nSen's Fortress=\nThe Duke's Archives=\nThe Duke's Archives (Insane)=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
