{"id": "133775", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133775", "title": "Black Blade", "text": "The Black Blade is a &lt;a href=\"Katanas%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;katana&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Catacombs%20of%20Carthus\"&gt;Catacombs of Carthus&lt;/a&gt;, dropped by the &lt;a href=\"Mimic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; at the end of the upper ledge surrounding the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;, near the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Blade is a &lt;a href=\"Katanas%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;katana&lt;/a&gt; with some simple trade-offs that lets it stand out as a unique weapon within its class. Its primary draw is its high damage, a &lt;a href=\"Sharp%20Gem\"&gt;Sharp&lt;/a&gt;-&lt;a href=\"Infusion\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt; Black Blade being one of the highest damage katanas available for a &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;-focused build, but it is somewhat short and heavy, and has a hefty strength requirement of 18 that may make it inaccessible for some builds.\nFurthermore, the weapon features different strong attacks to the standard katana moveset. Its one-handed strong attack combo is of particular note as it uses the standard attacks with their order reversed, starting with a horizontal slash that goes into a thrust. This gives it ready access to a faster alternative to the advancing slash of the &lt;a href=\"Hold\"&gt;Hold&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, at the cost of a less accessible thrust for distant opponents. This further reduces the effective reach of the weapon compared to other katanas, which may make it more difficult to fight opponents that are agile or who wield longer weapons such as &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spears&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ultra greatswords&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with .\nTrivia.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "31765", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31765", "title": "Black Boots", "text": "The Black Boots are a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". They are part of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Black Set&lt;/a&gt;. \nAvailability.\nThe whole set is gifted by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0after trading four or more boss souls with him. Straid can also be killed at any time, and the boots will be available from &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20Hag%20Melentia\"&gt;Merchant Hag Melentia&lt;/a&gt; for 4,800 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5289", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5289", "title": "Black Bow of Pharis", "text": "The Black Bow of Pharis is a &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Garden\"&gt;Darkroot Garden&lt;/a&gt;, it is dropped by the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20Hunter%20Archer\"&gt;Forest Hunter Archer&lt;/a&gt;. Killing her counts as a betrayal against the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20Hunter\"&gt;Forest Hunter&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; if the player is a member at that time.\nIf she dies by falling (or being kicked) off a cliff, reloading the game will cause the items that would have been dropped to appear on the spot where she first spawned.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Bow of Pharis has very high &lt;a href=\"range\"&gt;range&lt;/a&gt;. It has the highest &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"scaling\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; of any bow in the game, but low base damage and Strength scaling, making it better suited for Dex builds. The S scaling transfers to either &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Divine%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;divine&lt;/a&gt; paths, respectively.\nIts high scaling makes it ideal for upgrading along the Magic, Divine or &lt;a href=\"Occult%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Occult&lt;/a&gt; paths while using &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Arrow\"&gt;Moonlight Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s. Enchanted is not an optimal choice, as its damage falls behind Magic considerably, especially on builds with both high Intelligence and Dexterity. Divine and Occult have a negligible damage difference regardless of the wielder's Faith, meaning that the player should pick &lt;a href=\"upgrade%20path\"&gt;upgrade path&lt;/a&gt; based on if they want the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;Divine auxiliary effect&lt;/a&gt; or its &lt;a href=\"Occult%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;Occult counterpart&lt;/a&gt;. Notably, the Divine auxiliary effect will counteract the lowered damage dealt to &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s due to arrows dealing thrusting damage, on top of preventing them from resurrecting, while the occult effect will increase damage dealt to multiple durable opponents, such as &lt;a href=\"Sentinel\"&gt;Sentinel&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Slayer%20Ornstein%20and%20Executioner%20Smough\"&gt;Dragon Slayer Ornstein&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "130381", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130381", "title": "Black Bow of Pharis (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Bow of Pharis is a &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;. On the far left side of the swamp, three &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Ghru\"&gt;Elder Ghru&lt;/a&gt;s can be found congregating near the flame closest to the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep%23Bonfires\"&gt;Keep Ruins&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. One of them will automatically drop the bow into the player's inventory when killed.\nCharacteristics.\nCompared to the &lt;a href=\"Longbow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Longbow&lt;/a&gt;, the Black Bow of Pharis is a true sniper's weapon. It has the lowest base damage of all the bows in the game, but it makes up for this with its higher overall &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, particularly in &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, as well as its increased range. Where other bows may fail due to distance to the target, the Black Bow of Pharis will still accurately send full-power arrows to their destination, allowing the wielder to line up headshots with ease. When combined with the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hawk Ring&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Feather%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Feather Arrows&lt;/a&gt;, it can easily snipe foes from well outside of engagement range, while still dealing impressive damage."}
