{"id": "57338", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57338", "title": "Black Dragon Greatsword", "text": "The Black Dragon Greatsword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nTrivia.\nThe Black Dragon referred to in the item description could be referring to &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Kalameet\"&gt;Black Dragon Kalameet&lt;/a&gt;, who can be confronted by the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" when they are pulled back in time by &lt;a href=\"Manus%2C%20Father%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Manus&lt;/a&gt; in the \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC."}
{"id": "73613", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=73613", "title": "Black Dragon Helm", "text": "The Black Dragon Helm is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Set\"&gt;Black Dragon Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nIt is equipped upon usage of the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Head%20Stone\"&gt;Dragon Head Stone&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Torso%20Stone\"&gt;Dragon Torso Stone&lt;/a&gt;, and can only be removed by &lt;a href=\"dying\"&gt;dying&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "7689", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7689", "title": "Black Dragon Kalameet", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nThe player first encounters Kalameet on the second stone bridge in &lt;a href=\"Royal%20Wood\"&gt;Royal Wood&lt;/a&gt;.\nKalameet can be confronted opposite the Colosseum where &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Artorias\"&gt;Knight Artorias&lt;/a&gt; is fought. Beyond some &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Attack%20Dog\"&gt;Abyss Attack Dog&lt;/a&gt;s lies a ladder running parallel to a waterfall. Shortly after moving into the clearing, Kalameet will fly through the canyon and breathe black fire at the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt;. After this attack, speaking to &lt;a href=\"Hawkeye%20Gough\"&gt;Hawkeye Gough&lt;/a&gt; will convince him to shoot down Kalameet, so players can properly engage in battle on the ground. It is not necessary to be struck by the attack in order to receive Gough's help, only that Kalameet performs it.\nIt is possible to kill Kalameet without Gough's help. However, doing so will take an inordinately long time and a very large amount of arrows and the player will not receive any souls as a reward.\u00a0\nSummoning.\nAfter Gough shoots Kalameet down, the &lt;a href=\"Royal%20Wood\"&gt;Royal Wood&lt;/a&gt; (including the arena where players fought &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Artorias\"&gt;Knight Artorias&lt;/a&gt;) becomes Kalameet's summoning area. While &lt;a href=\"white%20phantom\"&gt;white phantom&lt;/a&gt;s become available for summoning (usually at the beginning of the Royal Wood, near &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Sanctuary\"&gt;Oolacile Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;), it means that red phantoms may &lt;a href=\"invade\"&gt;invade&lt;/a&gt; again also.\nLore.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nKalameet is a descendant of the primordial &lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;archdragons&lt;/a&gt;.\nDue to the appearance of \"Disparity\" and &lt;a href=\"Soul\"&gt;Soul&lt;/a&gt;s following the ignition of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; that allowed the evolution of life, Kalameet was born with unique characteristics compared to the original archdragons as he possessed a single orange eye, the ability to produce a high frequency noise which doubles the damage received by targets hit by this attack and an obsidian hide that makes him not only able to resist magic and fire like other dragons but even lightning which was their weak point.\nThanks to his extraordinary strength, Kalameet managed to survive the extermination of the Dragons caused by the &lt;a href=\"Lords\"&gt;Lords&lt;/a&gt; during the war and survived throughout the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Age of Fire&lt;/a&gt;. At some point, after &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt; was corrupted by the &lt;a href=\"Abyss\"&gt;Abyss&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Manus%2C%20Father%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Manus&lt;/a&gt;, the dragon took up residence in the area, and not even the mighty warriors left in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; dared to provoke his ire.\nHowever, at a certain point, a &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt; who ended up in Oolacile decided to challenge the black dragon and after a legendary battle managed to defeat him. From his tail they formed an &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Greatsword\"&gt;Obsidian Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; infused with the mystical power of the dragon and with his orange eye they created an &lt;a href=\"Calamity%20Ring\"&gt;enchanted ring&lt;/a&gt; that doubled the damaged received by its wearer.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough Kalameet was defeated and killed, a group of knights found his corpse and used his scales to create &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Helm\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; close to the appearance of the dragon, while they used his talons to craft &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Shield\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt; and his tail to forge &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Greataxe\"&gt;several&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Warpick\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Sword\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;. As the centuries passed, the Black Dragon became considered a mere legend in which he was defeated by a brave warrior in a magnificent battle and that his tail was used to forge legendary weapons. In the region of &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt; the name of Kalameet has been long lost and, while the legend of the &lt;a href=\"Seath%20the%20Scaleless\"&gt;pale dragon&lt;/a&gt; is told in various locales even if each account is fragmentary, the Black Dragon is rarely mentioned and some even say that it is only an an embellishment adopted in later retellings of the story.\nDespite this, the group of knights known as the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; who wore armor forged from the scales of Kalameet and used weapons created from his tail continued to exist and at some point arrived in Drangleic and settled in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;. The group of knights would also join the &lt;a href=\"Covenants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Remnants\"&gt;Dragon Remnants&lt;/a&gt;, apostles who venerated the primordial creatures and desired the perpetuity of their existence, seeking their scales to rise above their limited human existence. This group used the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Eye%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dragon Eyes&lt;/a&gt; to invade the space and time of other knights and challenge them to claim their dragon scales, rewarding the best among them with the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Torso%20Stone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stones infused with the powers of the dragons&lt;/a&gt; to try to achieve transformation and the ancient &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Greatsword\"&gt;Black Dragon Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; forged with Kalameet's tail.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough the \n&lt;a href=\"Calamity%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;calamitous ring&lt;/a&gt; created with the eye of Kalameet had no useful power and was actually only dangerous, the artifact continued to be passed down for thousands of years as a symbol of dragon worship. Its most fervent adherents even becoming convinced that the task of preserving it had been bestowed upon them as a sacred duty. \nLike many other artifacts and beings connected to the ancient dragons, the ring of Kalameet also ended up at &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;, a place where the remnants of the &lt;a href=\"Man%20Serpent\"&gt;men-serpents&lt;/a&gt; and the dragon worshippers had gathered to venerate the primordial beings and attempted to achieve their perfect shape using &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Head%20Stone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stones&lt;/a&gt; imbued with the power of everlasting dragons. The ring was thus kept in front of the statue of one of those who, in meditation, had managed to partially achieve the draconic transformation.\nObsidian Greatsword.\nSevering Kalameet's tail and obtaining the &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Greatsword\"&gt;Obsidian Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; can often prove more challenging than the battle itself, as the dragon's tail is mostly out of reach throughout the fight. His tail has 540 health on Ng and 847 health on NG+.\nBoss information.\nAttacks.\nHellfire Sweep.\nUsed only if the player attempts to enter the gorge before having Hawkeye Gough shoot down Kalameet. Kalameet flies overhead and bathes the entire area in flame then flies away. He will continue to use this attack as long as the player stays in the gorge.\nStraight Flame.\nTriggered when at long range, Black Dragon Kalameet will direct his flames toward the player. This does not track, so it can be easily avoided. Being caught in the flame will often result in a stun-lock, fatal outcome. Blocking will result in a guard break unless the player has a strong shield and high stamina. Kalameet may stunlock the player and use this attack between 1-3 times in a row which will result in a quick death.\nSweeping Flame.\nWhen the player is in medium range of Black Dragon Kalameet, he will breath a surge of his flame, sweeping it from his left to his right. This is a good opportunity to rush and strike him where he is open, but blocking is also possible.\nClose Range Flame.\nWhen the player is under Kalameet's head, he will stand on his back legs and breath fire in a large area right in front of him. A safe spot is to rush under his head or between his legs.\nRising Inferno.\nTriggered when the player is very close and is one of Black Dragon Kalameet's most devastating attacks. He will fly upwards into the air and hover, before breathing fire directly below him. The flame spreads in a circular pattern from the impact point and deals an extreme amount of damage. Running away is recommended, although blocking is also possible with &lt;a href=\"greatshields\"&gt;greatshields&lt;/a&gt;. Shields will take two hits in close proximity and a single hit further away.\nThis can be particularly frustrating, due to the lock-on breaking right at the edge of the danger zone. This causes players trying to run away to turn back into the line-of-fire, or blocking players to turn their backs to the flames. The best way to prevent the lock-on from breaking is to back away from Kalameet as soon as possible. Blocking players may choose to simply stand their ground to avoid breaking the lock. This can also be avoided by simply unlocking and running, or continually rolling away when Kalameet shows signs of the attack.\nFlame Feint.\nKalameet will lunge past the player and once behind them turn around to sweep the area in front of him with fire. When Kalameet lunges however he will usually go far past the player, making the latter part of the attack harmless. Players can take this opportunity to heal or cast spells. If the player stands in the way when Kalameet lunges they can still take considerable damage from the collision.\nIf a wall is behind the player, it will stop Black Dragon Kalameet's progress, leaving him in the player's near vicinity. This is extremely unsafe, as it will put the player in a position where escaping the flame is not possible.\nHead Strike.\nWhen the player is near, Kalameet will swing with his head from his right side to his left, using his snout as a spear. He may afterwards follow up with a swing in the reverse direction. This can be blocked, however. Due to Kalameet's long neck, the second swing has a tendency to strike the player in the back if they are too close.\nHis right flank is safe during this and leaves him open for attack.\nFoot Stomp.\nWhen the player is too close to Kalameet's anterior underside, he will stomp his feet. These stomps don't reach out to the player, so just not being directly under Black Dragon Kalameet is enough to avoid this attack.\nTail Smash.\nBlack Dragon Kalameet will attempt to crush players with his tail if they remain underneath or behind him long enough. Kalameet's tail will remain on the ground for several seconds, providing one of the best opportunities to cut his tail off.\nRush Strike.\nSimilar to the &lt;a href=\"%23Head%20Strike\"&gt;Head Strike&lt;/a&gt;, but without the follow up and covers a greater distance; Black Dragon Kalameet will lunge forward, swiping the player with his head and claw. This attack can be surprising, as he throws it very fast and from a rather long distance. Blocking is possible, but will greatly push the player back.\nEvasive Tail Whip.\nBlack Dragon Kalameet will speedily rotate in a full circle, swinging his tail at the player while jumping away. The actual tail sweep comes late, making difficult to time dodges correctly.\nThis is similar to &lt;a href=\"Great%20Grey%20Wolf%20Sif\"&gt;Great Grey Wolf Sif's&lt;/a&gt; attack.\nSwooping Charge.\nBlack Dragon Kalameet will rise off the ground before charging at the player. Players can take damage from the swoop itself, by being under Black Dragon Kalameet when he lands, or by both in succession.\nKalameet is most likely to use Tail Smash or Tail Sweep after this attack.\nMark of Calamity.\nBlack Dragon Kalameet's signature move. He will rise on his hind legs while the crest on his head glows intensely and produces a high frequency noise. If captured the player will then levitate in front of Kalameet and receive some damage. Afterwards, the player will have the Mark of Calamity for about 60 seconds, during which they will receive twice as much damage. Players can avoid this by running away as soon as he begins to stand.\nMusic.\n&lt;embedvideo service=\"youtube\" alignment=\"center\" description=\"Dark Souls \u2014 Kalameet by \"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9fzftmoOpTY&lt;/embedvideo&gt;"}
{"id": "73623", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=73623", "title": "Black Dragon Leggings", "text": "The Black Dragon Leggings are a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".&lt;br&gt;They are part of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Set\"&gt;Black Dragon Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nThey are equipped upon usage of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Torso%20Stone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dragon Torso Stone&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0along with the rest of the Black Dragon Set. They can only be removed by dying."}
{"id": "68758", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=68758", "title": "Black Dragon Set", "text": "The Black Dragon Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAchieve Rank 2 in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Remnants\"&gt;Dragon Remnants&lt;/a&gt; by offering 20 &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scale%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;dragon scales&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in order to receive the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Head%20Stone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dragon Head&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Torso%20Stone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Torso Stones&lt;/a&gt;. Using the Head Stone equips the helmet and the Torso Stone will equip the entire set, including the helmet.\nCharacteristics.\nCannot be upgraded. Provides fair &lt;a href=\"physical%20defence\"&gt;physical defence&lt;/a&gt; and excellent &lt;a href=\"elemental%20defense\"&gt;elemental defense&lt;/a&gt; at an incredibly low &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, however the armor set has 0 &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, making a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; like the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Giants\"&gt;Ring of Giants&lt;/a&gt; +2 needed. Wearer cannot take off this armor set, but it will be removed automatically upon &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;. However, should the player want to remove it without becoming &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;ed, dying while a &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Life%20Protection\"&gt;Ring of Life Protection&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0is equipped will remove the armor at the cost of having to repair the ring. Alternatively, it is possible to enter the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinels\"&gt;Blue Sentinels&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Brotherhood%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Brotherhood of Blood&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenants&lt;/a&gt; and duel within the arenas at their respective locations. After doing so, simply lose the battle, causing the armor to be removed without loss of &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Souls&lt;/a&gt;. The player may also leave a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;summon&lt;/a&gt; sign\u00a0to be summoned into another world and then die, this will produce the same results.\nAfter the Black Dragon Set is equipped, using the Dragon Head Stone makes the player breathe &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; and using the Dragon Torso Stone releases a shockwave similar to &lt;a href=\"Force%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Force&lt;/a&gt;, while also giving the player a damage buff for 5 seconds. Both of these actions drain &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;, but while the fire breath is exhausted in a continuous rate, the damage buff will empty a large portion of the player's stamina bar. The stamina cost is set, and as such; the stamina loss is more manageable with high &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "61889", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=61889", "title": "Black Dragon Shield", "text": "The Black Dragon Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt; (3%).\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Dragon Shield is a very powerful all-around shield with strong elemental defenses, allowing it to reliably block almost all forms of damage. Its decent stability makes it useful for warding off most forms of physical attacks.\nHowever, it is also only available as a random drop in the very last area in the main game, meaning that its utility will be very limited. As well, like all other Black Dragon equipment, it requires the use of &lt;a href=\"Petrified%20Dragon%20Bone\"&gt;Petrified Dragon Bone&lt;/a&gt; to upgrade. Finally, it is one of the heavier medium shields in the game, meaning that equipping it may negatively impact players' mobility and equipment options."}
{"id": "57559", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57559", "title": "Black Dragon Sword", "text": "The Black Dragon Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Black Dragon Sword is a rare drop (0.5%) from the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; wielding the sword in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt; near the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Dragon\"&gt;Ancient Dragon&lt;/a&gt;. Using lots of &lt;a href=\"Item%20Discovery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;item discovery&lt;/a&gt; to get it is recommended.\nCharacteristics.\nAs with all Black Dragon &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, they have no &lt;a href=\"scaling\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, which means they are great choices for &lt;a href=\"infusing\"&gt;infusing&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Raw\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt; if the player is low level; infuse it with &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Enchant&lt;/a&gt;, if they have high &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;; or infusing with &lt;a href=\"Old%20Mundane%20Stone\"&gt;Mundane&lt;/a&gt; if they have very balanced stats.\nThey are upgraded with &lt;a href=\"Petrified%20Dragon%20Bone\"&gt;Petrified Dragon Bone&lt;/a&gt;s and their increase in damage when fully maxed out, is more than double their initial damage."}
{"id": "52465", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52465", "title": "Black Dragon Warpick", "text": "The Black Dragon Warpick\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nAs with all Black Dragon &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, they have no &lt;a href=\"scaling\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, which means they are great choices for &lt;a href=\"infusing\"&gt;infusing&lt;/a&gt; with\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Raw\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt; or various elements. Unlike dragon weapons in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", which are weaker to compensate for their lack of scaling, these are just better than a standard weapon and have higher durability to boot, fitting their legendary status. They are some of the game's best weapons, if you can get them to drop.\nThey are upgraded with\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Petrified%20Dragon%20Bone\"&gt;Petrified Dragon Bone&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0and their increase in damage when fully maxed out, is more than half their initial damage."}
{"id": "135639", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135639", "title": "Black Dress", "text": "The Black Dress is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Set&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "6842", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6842", "title": "Black Eye Orb", "text": "The Black Eye Orb is a summon item in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound outside &lt;a href=\"Anastacia%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Anastacia of Astora's&lt;/a&gt; cage in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Lautrec%20the%20Embraced\"&gt;Lautrec&lt;/a&gt; murders her, which triggers when either the &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20Soul\"&gt;Fire Keeper Soul&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0is collected by the player, or after both &lt;a href=\"Bells%20of%20Awakening\"&gt;Bells of Awakening&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0are rung.\nGeneral Information.\nWhen in the main chamber before the fight with &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Slayer%20Ornstein%20and%20Executioner%20Smough\"&gt;Dragon Slayer Ornstein and Executioner Smough&lt;/a&gt;, the player will receive a notification telling them that the Black Eye Orb is quivering. At this point, the player may invade Lautrec's world to combat him and his two companions, a &lt;a href=\"Lautrec%27s%20Comrade%2C%20Sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lautrec%27s%20Comrade%2C%20Warrior\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt;. If the player successfully kills Lautrec, they are awarded Anastacia's &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20Soul\"&gt;Fire Keeper Soul&lt;/a&gt;. Restoring it to Anastacia's cage revives her and re-ignites the &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. Alternately, it can be consumed for five &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20Mechanic\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt; or used to upgrade &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Estus Flasks&lt;/a&gt;, just like any other Fire Keeper Soul.\nSimilar to the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Eye%20Orb\"&gt;Blue Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt;s, the Black Eye Orb can be used if the player is in Hollow form.\nRemoved Content.\nA Black Eye Orb was also designated for &lt;a href=\"Shiva%20of%20the%20East\"&gt;Shiva of the East&lt;/a&gt; originally, but was removed before the final game was released.\nThe cut Black Eye Orb is displayed as Black Eye Orb (Shiva) in the ingame inventory. This orb is only obtainable by modding or save editing and if used in the courtyard area of &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;, you can invade Shiva as originally intended. Shiva will be accompanied by his bodyguard during the invasion event."}
{"id": "133945", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133945", "title": "Black Eye Orb (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Eye Orb is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;. The player must first join &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%27s%20Fingers\"&gt;Rosaria's Fingers&lt;/a&gt; and offer at least one &lt;a href=\"Pale%20Tongue\"&gt;Pale Tongue&lt;/a&gt; to rank up in the &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;. The player must then talk to &lt;a href=\"Ringfinger%20Leonhard\"&gt;Ringfinger Leonhard&lt;/a&gt;, who will appear at the entrance of &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep%23Bonfires\"&gt;Rosaria's Bed Chamber&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the player reaches &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; and defeats &lt;a href=\"Aldrich%2C%20Devourer%20of%20Gods\"&gt;Aldrich, Devourer of Gods&lt;/a&gt;, the orb can be found on the now-dead body of &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%2C%20Mother%20of%20Rebirth\"&gt;Rosaria&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nUsed to invade &lt;a href=\"Ringfinger%20Leonhard\"&gt;Leonhard&lt;/a&gt; in the room above the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley%23Bonfires\"&gt;Aldrich, Devourer of Gods&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"Gwynevere%2C%20Princess%20of%20Sunlight\"&gt;Gwynevere&lt;/a&gt;'s chamber in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\"). Upon defeating him in his world, the player will obtain the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Rosaria\"&gt;Soul of Rosaria&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Crescent%20Moon%20Sword\"&gt;Crescent Moon Sword&lt;/a&gt; and his &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Mask\"&gt;Silver Mask&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "133566", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133566", "title": "Black Fire Orb", "text": "Black Fire Orb is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Karla\"&gt;Karla&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once she has been given the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Warden%20Pyromancy%20Tome\"&gt;Grave Warden Pyromancy Tome&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nHurls a black fireball at the target, inflicting 2.4 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage. Enemies caught in the explosion at the impact point rather than being hit by the fireball itself will take only 2.2 times the Spell Buff of the catalyst as Dark damage.\nUse.\nSingle player.\nAs with the other Dark Pyromancies, Black Fire Orb is useful for bringing an additional damage type to the table against enemies that are resistant to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. While it is not as efficient as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Orb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Orb&lt;/a&gt; in terms of &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; cost-to-damage ratio, it is still a very useful tool to have on hand.\nOnline gameplay.\nWhile it is not nearly as damaging as &lt;a href=\"Great%20Chaos%20Fire%20Orb\"&gt;Great Chaos Fire Orb&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Bed%20Vestiges\"&gt;Chaos Bed Vestiges&lt;/a&gt; in terms of raw damage, Black Fire Orb is still quite useful in that it only requires a single &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot and does not cost an exorbitant amount of FP to cast. As well, it is the only orb-type projectile available that can be augmented by wearing the &lt;a href=\"Blindfold%20Mask\"&gt;Blindfold Mask&lt;/a&gt;, giving it an edge over most other Pyromancies. Ironically, this spell is also adept at dealing with opponents who are wearing the Blindfold Mask, as they will incur additional damage from Dark sources.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "2112", "revid": "357149", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2112", "title": "Black Firebomb", "text": "Black Firebombs are &lt;a href=\"offensive%20items\"&gt;offensive items&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". They are projectile weapons and are more powerful variants of &lt;a href=\"Firebomb\"&gt;Firebomb&lt;/a&gt;s.\nGeneral information.\nBlack firebombs have a flat fire attack of 250.\nBlack Firebombs as one's starting gift are a particularly reliable method to defeat the &lt;a href=\"Asylum%20Demon\"&gt;Asylum Demon&lt;/a&gt; on a first playthrough and obtain the &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;Demon's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nBlack Firebombs are very powerful early in the game. The damage they deal is enough to make them competitive as useful utility items throughout the middle of the game. However, at higher levels their relative damage may be considered lackluster."}
{"id": "70435", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=70435", "title": "Black Firebomb (Dark Souls II)", "text": "A Black Firebomb is an &lt;a href=\"Offensive%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;offensive item&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nBlack Firebombs are more powerful versions of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Firebomb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Firebombs&lt;/a&gt;. When thrown, the Black Firebomb can fly a fair distance and will explode on contact, dealing damage to &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in a small area. The damage can be increased by raising the player's &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; bonus, which is increased by improving one or both of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;.\nBeing more powerful than the standard Firebomb, they can be considered a straight upgrade from them. They are sold for only 100 more &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; than the weaker variant, meaning that they can prove to be both useful and cheap."}
{"id": "131280", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131280", "title": "Black Firebomb (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Black Firebombs are a throwable in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nThrow it at the enemy to deal great &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage (compared to the &lt;a href=\"Firebomb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firebombs&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "163286", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=163286", "title": "Black Flame", "text": ""}
{"id": "7628", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7628", "title": "Black Flame (Dark Souls)", "text": "Black Flame (\u9ed2\u708e) is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound on a corpse in the &lt;a href=\"Chasm%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Chasm of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt; on the path to &lt;a href=\"Manus%2C%20Father%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Manus&lt;/a&gt;, it is found down a path marked by a &lt;a href=\"Prism%20Stone%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Prism Stone&lt;/a&gt;. The corpse is guarded by several &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20Phantom\"&gt;Humanity Phantoms&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nConjures a burst of black fire from the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt;, which has fire attack power of 2.0 times the flame's magic adjust and physical attack power of 1.6 times the flame's magic adjust. Black Flame is almost identical to &lt;a href=\"Great%20Combustion\"&gt;Great Combustion&lt;/a&gt;, with identical numbers of casts, similar damage, and identical casting time. The only significant differences are their appearances and Black Flame's considerably higher &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; drain against opponents that block the attack. Black Flame can be deflected with the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Pendant\"&gt;Silver Pendant&lt;/a&gt;, but is difficult as per timing.\nThe increased stamina drain is extremely prominent when using a lower &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;. For example, a 50 stability shield will do roughly 2.8 times the stamina damage compared to Great Combustion. However, this also means that each point of stability has a huge effect on the final stamina drain. For example, an 80 stability shield will roughly match the stamina drain of Great Combustion on a 50 stability shield.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "133563", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133563", "title": "Black Flame (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Black Flame is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Karla\"&gt;Karla&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once she has been given the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Warden%20Pyromancy%20Tome\"&gt;Grave Warden Pyromancy Tome&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nCreates a dark explosion from the palm of the caster's hand, inflicting 2.4 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage. If a target is only caught in the flames lingering after the initial explosion, they will take only 2.2 times the Spell Buff of the catalyst as Dark damage.\nUse.\nSingle player.\nAs it is one of only three Dark Pyromancies in the game, Black Flame is extremely useful for bringing another damage type to the table. Its fast casting speed makes it a force to be reckoned with, though being a melee range spell hampers its utility somewhat. Like all other Combustion-type spells, it benefits from being cast from a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancer%27s%20Parting%20Flame\"&gt;Pyromancer's Parting Flame&lt;/a&gt; for the extra melee-range damage.\nOnline gameplay.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, this spell is a favorite, as it inflicts extremely high &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; damage if blocked, enough to threaten even &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshields&lt;/a&gt; with a guard break. This is extremely useful for dispatching opposing players with &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ripostes&lt;/a&gt;, particularly as an invader who has to fight multiple opponents and needs to even the odds in an efficient manner.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
