{"id": "144056", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=144056", "title": "Black Hand Gotthard", "text": "Black Hand Gotthard is a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nA hunter who served several kings of &lt;a href=\"Lothric\"&gt;Lothric&lt;/a&gt;. He held the title of \"Black Hand\", a title that is only bestowed upon hunters that serve successive kings. To date, only three have obtained this title (&lt;a href=\"Black%20Hand%20Kamui\"&gt;Black Hand Kamui&lt;/a&gt; is one and the other is unknown).\nHe was able to obtain said title due to his expert swordsmanship. Eventually, due to the decaying state of the kingdom, he attempted to escape &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Castle\"&gt;Lothric Castle&lt;/a&gt;, though he did not succeed. He wears the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Hand%20Set\"&gt;Black Hand Set&lt;/a&gt; and wields the &lt;a href=\"Gotthard%20Twinswords\"&gt;Gotthard Twinswords&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Castle\"&gt;Lothric Castle&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "135594", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135594", "title": "Black Hand Hat", "text": "The Black Hand Hat is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Hand%20Set\"&gt;Black Hand Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for 3,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; after defeating &lt;a href=\"Black%20Hand%20Kamui\"&gt;Black Hand Kamui&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Grand Archives&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "137706", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137706", "title": "Black Hand Kamui", "text": "Black Hand Kamui is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nOne of the three \"Black Hands\", together with &lt;a href=\"Black%20Hand%20Gotthard\"&gt;Black Hand Gotthard&lt;/a&gt; and an unknown member. He wears the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Hand%20Set\"&gt;Black Hand Set&lt;/a&gt; and wields &lt;a href=\"Onikiri%20and%20Ubadachi\"&gt;Onikiri and Ubadachi&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nAttacks in the large courtyard after exiting the rooftops section of the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Grand Archives&lt;/a&gt;, together with &lt;a href=\"Lion%20Knight%20Albert\"&gt;Lion Knight Albert&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Daughter%20of%20Crystal%20Kriemhild\"&gt;Daughter of Crystal Kriemhild&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nA strategy that can be applied to all three of them is the use of &lt;a href=\"Dung%20Pie%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dung Pies&lt;/a&gt;. Make a run for the elevator shortcut and reload the area; they will be visible from the elevator exit and will not trigger from this position unless damaged by a weapon. Since Dung Pies inflict &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; build-up but don't cause physical damage, they can be thrown without triggering them. They can quickly be killed afterward with a &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Throwing Knife&lt;/a&gt; once their health has been depleted.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; decides to take them on head on, try luring over one at a time first and get some free hits in."}
{"id": "135165", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135165", "title": "Black Hand Set", "text": "The Black Hand Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe hat and armor are sold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for a total of 7,500 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; after defeating &lt;a href=\"Black%20Hand%20Kamui\"&gt;Black Hand Kamui&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Grand Archives&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe gloves and trousers are sold by &lt;a href=\"Greirat%20of%20the%20Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Greirat of the Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; for a total of 3,000 souls after he returns from pillaging the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;. The Shrine Handmaid will also sell them at this price should she be given &lt;a href=\"Greirat%27s%20Ashes\"&gt;Greirat's Ashes&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nAn upgraded version of the &lt;a href=\"Assassin%20Set\"&gt;Assassin Set&lt;/a&gt;, the Black Hand Set provides generally augmented defenses across the board except against &lt;a href=\"Strike\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage, while also slightly increasing the &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;. Its main strengths are defense against &lt;a href=\"Slash\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; damage, as well as &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;. As well, it increases resistance against &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; by a significant amount."}
