{"id": "4292", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4292", "title": "Black Iron Greatshield", "text": "The Black Iron Greatshield is a &lt;a href=\"greatshield\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Black Iron Greatshield can be found on a corpse, in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, on the bottom floor near the painting in the cathedral, guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Painting%20Guardian\"&gt;Painting Guardian&lt;/a&gt; (along with the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Set\"&gt;Black Iron Set&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Greatsword\"&gt;Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;).\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Iron Greatshield is essentially a heavier, slightly less &lt;a href=\"stable\"&gt;stable&lt;/a&gt; version of the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20Shield\"&gt;Tower Shield&lt;/a&gt; but with the best &lt;a href=\"fire%20defense\"&gt;fire defense&lt;/a&gt; of all the Greatshields. This shield has a heavy deflection and a standard bash attack. The &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; is 23.\nResistance defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking.\nTrivia.\nThe Black Iron Greatshield is labeled as a &lt;a href=\"Standard%20Shields\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt; rather than a &lt;a href=\"Greatshield\"&gt;Greatshield&lt;/a&gt; as its weapon type. This is most likely an error by programmers, as the name and description imply that it is a Greatshield."}
{"id": "133463", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133463", "title": "Black Iron Greatshield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Iron Greatshield is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by defeating &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Slayer%20Tsorig\"&gt;Knight Slayer Tsorig&lt;/a&gt; by the large lava pool in the &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake%23Bonfires\"&gt;Demon Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, beneath the &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Iron Greatshield is a specialized greatshield that is effective against enemies that deal &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. Its respectable stability, low weight and 100% physical damage absorption also make it an ideal greatshield for defending against physical attacks. Because many enemies in the game are capable of dealing fire damage with various attacks, the Black Iron Greatshield is very effective at protecting players against threats in &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Castle\"&gt;Lothric Castle&lt;/a&gt;, such as the hollows wielding &lt;a href=\"Firebomb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firebombs&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Exploding%20Bolt\"&gt;Exploding Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s, and the &lt;a href=\"Thrall\"&gt;Thrall&lt;/a&gt;s wielding fire-infused weapons. It can be particularly useful against bosses that deal physical and fire damage, such as the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Demon%20King\"&gt;Old Demon King&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Princes\"&gt;Lorian, Elder Prince&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Prince\"&gt;Demon Prince&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, this greatshield's primary weakness is its low &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; defense, barely absorbing half of any lightning damage that it blocks. This can make it a poor choice against certain foes, particularly &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Armour\"&gt;Dragonslayer Armour&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nameless%20King\"&gt;Nameless King&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
