{"id": "7783", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7783", "title": "Black Iron Set", "text": "The Black Iron Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". \nAvailability.\nFound on a corpse next to the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Painting%20Guardian\"&gt;Painting Guardian&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nWorn by the hero &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Tarkus\"&gt;Black Iron Tarkus&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Iron Set is relatively light-&lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; compared to other &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;heavy armor sets&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0and has correspondingly lower damage resistance, excluding &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; resistance and &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. When fully upgraded however, its &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Damage%20Types\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; defenses are second only to the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Set\"&gt;Giant Set&lt;/a&gt; and it provides the highest Flame Defense of any &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;armor set&lt;/a&gt;. It also has the second-highest &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance of any heavy set, behind only &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Set\"&gt;Havel's Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe Black Iron Set is one of the two &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Heavy Sets&lt;/a&gt; that can be upgraded, along with the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Set\"&gt;Giant Set&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "135166", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135166", "title": "Black Iron Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Iron Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for a total of 21,500 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; after defeating &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Slayer%20Tsorig\"&gt;Knight Slayer Tsorig&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nAlthough it weighs in at the higher end of heavy armor sets, the Black Iron Set provides very strong protection against most forms of physical and elemental damage. It is extremely resilient against all forms of physical damage save for &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt;, which is comparable to levels of protection offered mainly by medium armored sets. Its elemental defenses are fairly well-rounded, and it is exceptionally strong against &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. It can resist &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; buildup quite well across the board, only really being weak to &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt;.\nMost importantly, it offers a very strong &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;-to-weight ratio, with enough poise to trade against most other ultra weapons, when wielding an ultra-class weapon."}
{"id": "2140", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2140", "title": "Black Iron Tarkus", "text": "Black Iron Tarkus, (\u9ed2\u9244\u306e\u30bf\u30eb\u30ab\u30b9 \"Kurogane no Tarukasu\") also referred to as Iron Tarkus, is a &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and summon-able &lt;a href=\"white%20phantom\"&gt;white phantom&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". He can be summoned by the player in the fight against the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nIn a tower structure at the end of the walkway to the right from where the fog door to the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt; is located. Like other summon signs, Tarkus's summon sign is only visible if the player has not put down a summon sign and is in human form. He aids the player in taking on the Iron Golem as a &lt;a href=\"Phantom\"&gt;white phantom&lt;/a&gt;. He is notoriously tough and can serve as a distraction during the battle. In fact, Tarkus can defeat the boss all by himself in the first playthrough and stands a break-even chance of doing so on &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus\"&gt;future play throughs&lt;/a&gt; with minimal support from the player. A &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Set\"&gt;Black Iron Set&lt;/a&gt; is found on his corpse in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, next to the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Painting%20Guardian\"&gt;Painting Guardian&lt;/a&gt; stands next to his corpse, possibly removing it from the room since the body is so far away from the entrance.\nLore.\nBlack Iron Tarkus is the strongest &lt;a href=\"Berenike%20Knight\"&gt;Berenike Knight&lt;/a&gt;. Berenike Knights were known for their &lt;a href=\"Steel%20Set\"&gt;heavy armor of steel&lt;/a&gt; and used ultra heavy &lt;a href=\"Tower%20Shield\"&gt;Tower Shield&lt;/a&gt;s forged with thick plates of iron, favoring hard defense and stability, and gigantic swords capable of causing monstrous damage. and for their immense strength they were extolled as the mightiest of mighty. Tarkus was renowned even among his fellow knights for his great strength and he wore an &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Set\"&gt;ultra heavy armor&lt;/a&gt; made of special black iron so heavy that only he was able to wear it but that provided him with a strong defense against fire and his &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Greatshield\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, made of the same material, was even heavier than that of his fellow knights.\nHowever as the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; started to fade countless among the ranks of the &lt;a href=\"Berenike%20Knight\"&gt;Berenike Knight&lt;/a&gt;s became Undead and ventured to &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt;. Here they tried to make their way toward Anor Londo, through the only possible access: &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;. The knights of Berenike and Tarkus thus entered the dangerous proving ground but for naught as through decades of failure they were not able to advance and ended up as &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;s, becoming a threat to all the other Undead in the location. After a grueling and long battle, Tarkus eventually managed to reach the end of the path of Sen's Fortress and challenge the last trial in the form of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt;. The mighty knight in black iron armor managed to defeat even the guardian of Anor Londo, thus gaining access to the city of the gods. Despite his immense strength, once he reached Anor Londo, Tarkus perished at the hands of the &lt;a href=\"Painting%20Guardian\"&gt;Painting Guardian&lt;/a&gt;s before he could reach \"&lt;a href=\"Gwynevere%2C%20Princess%20of%20Sunlight\"&gt;Gwynevere, Princess of Sunlight&lt;/a&gt;\" and obtain the &lt;a href=\"Lordvessel\"&gt;Lordvessel&lt;/a&gt; and the few Berenite Knights that followed him ended up trapped inside the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter an unknown and immense amount of time, &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Slayer%20Tsorig\"&gt;Knight Slayer Tsorig&lt;/a&gt; found the black iron &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; of the deceased Tarkus and made them his own, becoming infamously known for their appearance, as the super heavy armor and shield were a signal of his mighty strenght."}
{"id": "2135", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2135", "title": "Black Knight", "text": "Black Knights are powerful in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocations.\nWith the exception of the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;final area&lt;/a&gt;, Black Knights are unique enemies that do not respawn. They can be found in the following locations throughout &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt;:\nDescription.\nBlack Knights are encountered, individually, in many areas of the game as non-respawning challenges for players. At the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;, however, they do respawn.\nThey wield various slow hitting but powerful weapons, the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Shield\"&gt;Black Knight Shield&lt;/a&gt; and wear the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Set\"&gt;Black Knight Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Black Knights were once the proud\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight\"&gt;Silver Knight&lt;/a&gt;s of &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Gwyn, Lord of Sunlight&lt;/a&gt;. Long ago they fought chaos demons and were charred black, also giving them high &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Damage%20Type%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; resistance. Many traveled with Lord Gwyn to the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;, and were burned to ashes when he linked the First Flame, wandering the world as disembodied spirits ever after. Their disembodied spirits can be seen roaming the stairs descending into the Kiln of the First Flame.\nStrategy.\nIt is usually not a good idea to take on Black Knights directly, as they have high &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; and can deal huge amounts of damage. Their attacks are slow, however, meaning that they are susceptible to &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Parry\"&gt;parries&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt's also advisable for lower level players to try and force them off ledges if possible (such as Undead Burg small bridge near bonfire or Darkroot Basin cliff) if killing them becomes problematic. This can either kill them or open them for a &lt;a href=\"Plunging%20Attack%23Dark%20Souls\"&gt;plunging attack&lt;/a&gt; to rack up some serious damage. One could also position themselves in front of a ledge, roll behind the knight as it attacks, and backstab it to knock it over the edge. If the knight dies from the fall, item drops will still be added to the players inventory like they would if the knight was killed normally.\nAttacking them from where they cannot reach or where they will not attack the player will make it easy to kill the knights with ranged attacks, such as &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"firebomb\"&gt;firebomb&lt;/a&gt;s.\nEnemy information.\nAttacks.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nAxe=\nGreatsword=\nHalberd=\nSword=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nDefenses.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nAxe-Knight=\nGreatsword-Knight=\nHalberd-Knight=\nSword-Knight=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nDrops.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nAxe-Knight=\nGreatsword-Knight=\nHalberd-Knight=\nSword-Knight=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "132289", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132289", "title": "Black Knight (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Black Knights are powerful in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nAlmost identical to their \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" counterparts, Black Knights continue to roam the world following their burning in the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;\nLore.\nFormer &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Silver Knights&lt;/a&gt; loyal to &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lord Gwyn&lt;/a&gt; who tragically were burned, their armors ending up charred, in their expedition to the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt; in Gwyn's desperate attempt to link the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;flame&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nBlacks Knights fight similarly to their counterparts in &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt;, although they are faster and more agile due to the enhanced combat mechanics. They are still very vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parries&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;backstabs&lt;/a&gt;, although they will attempt to shield-bash the player if they continually try to circle around them. If they manage to knock the player down, they can follow up with their slow uppercut attack, potentially killing the player while they are still getting up.\nThey are extremely weak to &lt;a href=\"Frostbite\"&gt;Frostbite&lt;/a&gt;, capable of being inflicted with the status effect in just two hits with an &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Straight%20Sword\"&gt;Irithyll Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt;. Inflicting them with the status effect will deal a sizable amount of damage upon proc as well, greatly diminishing the threat that they pose.\nThey wield either a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Greataxe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in combat and will attack other enemies if provoked."}
