{"id": "132975", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132975", "title": "Black Knight Glaive", "text": "The Black Knight Glaive is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nLocated in the &lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;, in the same arena where &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Gundyr\"&gt;Champion Gundyr&lt;/a&gt; is fought.\nThe halberd can be picked up before starting the boss fight. As one enters the arena, immediately turn right and hug the wall to find it.\nCharacteristics.\nLike all other weapons wielded by &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knights&lt;/a&gt;, the Black Knight Glaive is a powerhouse of destruction that can wreak havoc in the right hands.\nAs with its cousins, the Black Knight Glaive has high base damage and &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; well with both &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, making it a true quality weapon. However, unlike other Black Knight weaponry, the Glaive scales better with Dexterity than with Strength, meaning that it is more beneficial to keep both stats equalized. Also like its cousins, it possesses unique strong attacks that inflict increased &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; damage on targets, and in this case grants it a much stronger moveset due to not being burdened by an easily punishable two-handed strong attack.\nLike other Black Knight weapons, the Black Knight Glaive inflicts 20% more damage against &lt;a href=\"Demon%20%28lore%29\"&gt;demons&lt;/a&gt;. This makes it an ideal weapon for fighting enemies like the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Prince\"&gt;Demon Prince&lt;/a&gt;.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;\nTrivia.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "5154", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5154", "title": "Black Knight Greataxe", "text": "The Black Knight Greataxe is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped at a 20% rate by the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"The%20Catacombs\"&gt;The Catacombs&lt;/a&gt; which does not respawn, and the respawning Black Knight in the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Knight Greataxe has very high base damage and good &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"scaling\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, although like most &lt;a href=\"Unique%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, it cannot be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt;. Its heavy swings are very good for breaking &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"stunlock\"&gt;stunlock&lt;/a&gt;ing. It also does 20% more damage when used against &lt;a href=\"Demon%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt; type enemies. The Black Knight Great Axe often seems weaker in practice than its damage stats would indicate. This is because its Standard Attacks (R1/RB) have reduced damage to account for their swing speed, which is fast compared to similar weapons. The damage of its slower Power Attacks (R2/RT) are in line with its listed statistics. This Greataxe has lower &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Motion Values&lt;/a&gt; on its two handed attacks compared with other weapons in the Greataxe class. "}
{"id": "52447", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52447", "title": "Black Knight Greataxe (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Black Knight Greataxe is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Knight Greataxe is an interesting weapon, as it has the potential to be very powerful, yet can be quite difficult to use.\nLike all Black Knight weapons, this &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greataxe&lt;/a&gt; inflicts both physical and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, and scales decently with both. However, what sets this apart from the other Black Knight equipment is its raw damage potential; it can inflict an incredible amount of damage due to its high base damage, even with its mediocre scaling at base level. Upon upgrading the weapon, the strength scaling improves heavily, going from a C all the way to an A at +5, allowing it to be a formidable weapon.\nHowever, this weapon has two fatal drawbacks. The first drawback is that the weapon must, similarly to most &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Halberds&lt;/a&gt;, hit with the head of the axe to deal full damage. Hitting an opponent with the handle, results in underwhelming damage being dealt to them. This, coupled with its cumbersome moveset and high weight, can make the weapon very unreliable to use. Proper spacing is paramount if players wish to make the most out of this weapon, which can be a challenge in itself, especially in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt upgrades with &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the huge gap between physical and fire damage, &lt;a href=\"Infusion\"&gt;infusing&lt;/a&gt; this weapon with &lt;a href=\"Firedrake%20Stone\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; is a wise choice."}
{"id": "132973", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132973", "title": "Black Knight Greataxe (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Knight Greataxe is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped from the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knights&lt;/a&gt; who wield the weapon in &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA highly destructive weapon and potentially the most powerful of the greataxes, the Black Knight Greataxe is a tool of raw destruction that is capable of large amounts of destruction.\nAs a weapon wielded by Black Knights, it inflicts 20% more damage against &lt;a href=\"Demon%20%28lore%29\"&gt;demons&lt;/a&gt;. Even without this particular trait, it can inflict large amounts of damage against anything it hits, as it possesses the enhanced damage multipliers of the greataxe class on top of high base damage and strong &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; in both &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;. This damage can be further augmented by its skill, &lt;a href=\"Warcry\"&gt;Warcry&lt;/a&gt;, which becomes more potent if the wielder has large amounts of Strength. It is also the only greataxe that possesses a truly unique moveset, being capable of horizontal swings when one-handed and powerful vertical sweeps when two-handed, as opposed to the downward smashes that all other greataxes are restricted to. Being a Black Knight weapon, it also possesses unique strong attacks that inflict increased &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; damage to targets, making it a useful asset.\nHowever, like all other Black Knight weapons, it is extraordinarily heavy and costs large amounts of &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; to swing. As such, wielding this weapon requires great investments in not only Strength and Endurance but also &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "4989", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4989", "title": "Black Knight Greatsword", "text": "The Black Knight Greatsword is an &lt;a href=\"ultra%20greatsword\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Knight Greatsword deals very high damage and has the second highest &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"scaling\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; of all Ultra Greatswords, surpassed only by the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Great%20Machete\"&gt;Demon Great Machete&lt;/a&gt;. Like all Black Knight weapons, it deals an additional 20% damage to &lt;a href=\"Demon%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt; type enemies, but cannot be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;Enchanted&lt;/a&gt;. It is notable for having strong attacks that, whilst\u00a0extremely slow\u00a0to perform, potentially send foes flying backward or into the air; these attacks also do catastrophic damage. \nPlayers who have this sword drop early in Undead Parish should be aware that the full 32 Strength requirement is not needed and that two-handing this sword requires 22 Strength. "}
{"id": "51010", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51010", "title": "Black Knight Greatsword (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Black Knight Greatsword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nUnlike the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Sword\"&gt;Black Knight Sword&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", this greatsword is longer and deals &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage; the moveset is also different than the previous version of this blade.\nInterestingly, the Black Knight Greatsword requires more stamina to swing than many other &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatswords&lt;/a&gt;, but seems to only suffer this effect on R1 and R2s. Rolling and Running attacks appear to suffer no penalty."}
{"id": "133865", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133865", "title": "Black Knight Greatsword (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Knight Greatsword is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knights&lt;/a&gt; who wield it. One can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;, another in &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt; and two more in the &lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA powerhouse of an ultra greatsword, the Black Knight Greatsword brings raw power to the field that allows its wielder to toss foes aside like toys.\nAs with other unique &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, it possesses quality &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, and as an ultra greatsword it leans more towards &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; than &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;. It possesses the two-handed vertical &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;, and like other Black Knight weapons it has unique strong attacks that inflict increased &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; damage to targets. This makes it a very powerful asset when fighting other &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; weapons.\nUnique to this weapon, the Black Knight Greatsword possesses two power attacks that are capable of utterly decimating enemies. Its two-handed strong attack, when fully charged, is capable of knocking enemies skyward, similar to an &lt;a href=\"Stomp%20%28upward%29\"&gt;upward Stomp&lt;/a&gt;, requiring no &lt;a href=\"FP\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; but possessing no bonus &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; in exchange. And its actual &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Stomp%20%28downward%29\"&gt;downward Stomp&lt;/a&gt;, uses the weapon's broad side to utterly crush any foes foolish enough to engage the wielder.\nAs with other Black Knight weapons, it inflicts a bonus 20% damage against &lt;a href=\"Demons\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;-type enemies, making it a strong asset when fighting enemies like the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Demon%20King\"&gt;Old Demon King&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Prince\"&gt;Demon Prince&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4595", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4595", "title": "Black Knight Halberd", "text": "The Black Knight Halberd is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Black Knight Halberd is dropped at a 20% rare from Halberd wielding &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt;s. There are two non-respawning black knights that wield this weapon. One is in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt; and another is in the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt;. A respawning Black Knight is found near the end of the path in the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;. \nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Knight Halberd has high base damage however, it cannot be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; and is &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;heavier&lt;/a&gt; than some other Halberds, with considerably lower &lt;a href=\"scaling\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;. The benefits of this weapon mainly boil down to its high base damage and ease of fully upgrading early, it will fall off in the late game and NG+. If you would like a buffable clone of this weapon on the standard upgrade path try &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%27s%20Halberd\"&gt;Gargoyle's Halberd&lt;/a&gt;. Like all Black Knight weapons, it deals additional 20% damage to &lt;a href=\"Demon%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt; type enemies. \nThe menu lists the attack type as Slash, but a majority of attacks from this Halberd actually deal &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage and can benefit from &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt; to boost &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Counter_Damage\"&gt;counter damage&lt;/a&gt;. This Halberd has a stagger animation on whiff meaning it also gets &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Sweet_Spot_Damage_Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; bonus damage, similar to others within its class."}
