{"id": "135167", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135167", "title": "Black Knight Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Knight Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knights&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nReturning from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", the Black Knight Set is on the light end of heavy armor sets and provides very good defenses across the board.\nIt is highly resistant to most forms of physical damage, save for a comparative weakness to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage that is nonetheless higher than that found on many lighter sets. Its elemental resistances are respectable but somewhat low for its weight, though it is highly resistant to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. Its resistance to &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt; is quite moderate, having no particular weaknesses and being quite resistant to &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up.\nWhile it has a respectable &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;-to-weight ratio, the total amount of Poise provided largely limits its effectiveness to trading when supported by the innate poise health of an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; or larger."}
{"id": "4156", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4156", "title": "Black Knight Shield", "text": "The Black Knight Shield is a &lt;a href=\"medium%20shield\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Black Knight Shield is a semi-rare drop from the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nIn comparison to the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight%20Shield\"&gt;Silver Knight Shield&lt;/a&gt;, the Black Knight Shield is slightly inferior in terms of &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"magic%20defense\"&gt;magic defense&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;. However, it has the best defense against &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Defense\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; of any &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; in the game and still remains one of the best medium shields. The shield has a medium deflection and normal &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; speed.\nResistance defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking.\nUpgrades.\nRequires: Black Knight Shield +0, 2,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "134847", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134847", "title": "Black Knight Shield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Knight Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knights&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Knight Shield is one of the best medium &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt; in the game. It boasts high base &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; and impressive &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; absorption, allowing players to shrug off fire attacks with minimal &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; cost. Fully upgraded, its stability rivals that of &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshields&lt;/a&gt;, making it the best medium shield for blocking &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; attacks. Finally, its skill allows for the use of the &lt;a href=\"weapon%20art\"&gt;weapon art&lt;/a&gt; of the right-hand weapon, giving players a higher degree of flexibility in their moveset.\nHowever, it is also the heaviest medium shield in the game, requiring at least some investment in &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a respectable amount of &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; in order to wield effectively. Its &lt;a href=\"elemental%20resistance\"&gt;elemental resistance&lt;/a&gt;s are relatively average for a medium shield, absorbing comparatively little damage from attacks that do not deal physical or fire damage. Therefore, while the Black Knight Shield is very strong against physical threats and enemies that deal Fire damage, it is not highly effective against other elements."}
{"id": "4157", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4157", "title": "Black Knight Sword", "text": "The Black Knight Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSemi-common drop from &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt;s wielding the Black Knight Sword. One (non-respawning) is encountered midway through the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt;; two more are found in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Asylum\"&gt;Undead Asylum&lt;/a&gt; if revisited; two sword Black Knights respawn in the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Knight Sword deals a high amount of &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;. Its fairly good reach is offset by its cumbersome &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;. Like all Black Knight &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, it deals 20% bonus damage to &lt;a href=\"Demon%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;demons&lt;/a&gt;.\nSince the Black Knight Sword can be obtained so early in the game (if players are lucky and get the drop), it can be useful in early stages where its damage output is very high compared to other weapons found at that stage. While it can easily carry the player to the very end of the game, as well as &lt;a href=\"AotA\"&gt;the DLC&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Man-serpent%20Greatsword\"&gt;Man-serpent Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; is a better alternative that can be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;augmented&lt;/a&gt; and, more importantly, requires no Dexterity, allowing a character to put significant extra levels into a different stat."}
{"id": "131440", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131440", "title": "Black Knight Sword (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Knight Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;, behind an &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Ruins\"&gt;Demon Ruins&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, descend two sets of stairs to reach a big room with two &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Cleric\"&gt;Demon Cleric&lt;/a&gt;s. Turn right and proceed straightforward into a passage at the end. Hit the carved wall at the very end of this passage to reveal a hidden room with a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt; slaying a &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Ghru\"&gt;Ghru&lt;/a&gt;. The sword can be found inside.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Knight Sword is a very effective greatsword for quality builds, despite being un-&lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusable&lt;/a&gt; and un-buffable. Its &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; tends more towards &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, however due to its un-infusable nature it cannot take advantage of scaling bonuses past 40 in either category.\nIts &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; is composed mainly of slashes, as well as being capable of performing a &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; with the second one-handed strong attack. While it does not have an advantage in reach compared to other greatswords, its moveset still grants it good coverage against crowds as well as against single targets. As well, the strong attacks of the weapon, whether one-handed or two-handed, deal increased &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; damage, making it useful for staggering foes should the need arise.\nWhat sets the Black Knight Sword apart from its peers is its &lt;a href=\"weapon%20art\"&gt;weapon art&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Perseverance%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt;, which is normally only seen on &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;hammers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;great hammers&lt;/a&gt;. Combined with its impressive damage output and respectable swing speed, this allows players to stand their ground and out-trade opponents who try to contest their ground, even those wielding ultra weapons.\nThis weapon, as well all the other Black Knight weapons, inflict 20% bonus damage to &lt;a href=\"Demon%20%28lore%29\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;-type foes. This means that it is particularly effective against enemies such as the &lt;a href=\"Stray%20Demon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Stray Demon&lt;/a&gt; and even bosses like the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Prince\"&gt;Demon Prince&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "66617", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=66617", "title": "Black Knight Ultra Greatsword", "text": "The Black Knight Ultra Greatsword is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in a metal chest, along with &lt;a href=\"Great%20Fireball%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, in &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove Tseldora&lt;/a&gt;. The chest is located behind a door on the right side of the room with the descending &lt;a href=\"Parasite%20Spider\"&gt;spiders&lt;/a&gt;. The door can only be opened with the &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Key\"&gt;Brightstone Key&lt;/a&gt;, obtained by killing &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Tseldora\"&gt;Duke Tseldora&lt;/a&gt;.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Kobold\"&gt;Kobold&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;."}
