{"id": "7978", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7978", "title": "Black Separation Crystal", "text": "The Black Separation Crystal is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGranted to the player at the beginning of the game.\nGeneral information.\nHosts can use the Black Separation Crystal to banish friendly &lt;a href=\"phantom\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt;s. Phantoms, in turn, can use the Black Separation Crystal to return to their worlds.\nHosts cannot use the Black Separation Crystal to force hostile phantoms to return home. However, red and blue phantoms can still use the Black Separation Crystal to leave the host's world."}
{"id": "41955", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41955", "title": "Black Separation Crystal (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Black Separation Crystal is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nThe Black Separation Crystal allows players to send friendly\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;phantoms&lt;/a&gt; back to their own worlds.\nAs a phantom (either hostile or friendly), players can activate their Black Separation Crystal to return to their own world."}
