{"id": "133567", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133567", "title": "Black Serpent", "text": "Black Serpent (\u9ed2\u86c7) is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20High%20Lord%20Wolnir\"&gt;Soul of High Lord Wolnir&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nThe caster conjures a rippling black flame at their feet that surges forward and weaves across the ground, tracking on the locked-on target. Has minor homing capability, and inflicts 1.65 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage to enemies it passes through.\nUse.\nSingle player.\nThis &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; will only follow an opponent if it has been locked-on before casting the spell. Otherwise, the black flame will move in a random direction. This pyromancy can be useful, even if the target is not locked on, since the random movement of the flame makes the enemy break their attack while trying to avoid the spell. \nEnemies that use shields, such as &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20Knight\"&gt;Cathedral Knight&lt;/a&gt;s, have their &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Break\"&gt;blocks broken&lt;/a&gt; from this attack. This can be used to almost always perform &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;critical&lt;/a&gt; attacks on them, if the shield is hit as they block, making it easier to combat defense-based enemies.\nOnline gameplay.\nEven if this Pyromancy doesn't seem useful in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, it could be used effectively with enough &lt;a href=\"casting%20speed\"&gt;casting speed&lt;/a&gt;, a true combo (which the enemy will not be able to escape from once they are caught in) is possible by transitioning from Black Serpent to either &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Bed%20Vestiges\"&gt;Chaos Bed Vestiges&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Great%20Chaos%20Fire%20Orb\"&gt;Great Chaos Fire Orb&lt;/a&gt;. One can even combo &lt;a href=\"Great%20Chaos%20Fire%20Orb\"&gt;Great Chaos Fire Orb&lt;/a&gt; into &lt;a href=\"Great%20Combustion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Combustion&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Black%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Flame&lt;/a&gt;, but only when the opponent is in front of the player and is hit by both fireball and lava.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nNotes.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "7617", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7617", "title": "Black Set", "text": "The Black Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nPillaged off a corpse in the Annex portion of the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;, hanging from a collapsed wall on the exterior side of the central decayed tower. Can most easily be accessed after finding the &lt;a href=\"Annex%20Key\"&gt;Annex Key&lt;/a&gt;, although it is possible to reach it without the key.\nPlot.\nThe Black Set is worn by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Oswald%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Oswald of Carim&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and is closely associated with the goddess &lt;a href=\"Velka%2C%20Goddess%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Velka&lt;/a&gt;. The set found in the Painted World of Ariamis is just one example of the many ties Velka had with the area, others being the &lt;a href=\"Velka%27s%20Rapier\"&gt;Velka's Rapier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crow%20Demon\"&gt;Crow Demon&lt;/a&gt;s and the &lt;a href=\"Vow%20of%20Silence\"&gt;Vow of Silence&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0\nCharacteristics.\nThe entire set has no &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; and below average physical defense, but boasts above average &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistances.\nTrivia.\nThe Black Set is worn by &lt;a href=\"Oswald%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Oswald of Carim&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "53053", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53053", "title": "Black Set (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The\u00a0Black Set\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nReceived from &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0after trading four or more and then talking to him."}
{"id": "135169", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135169", "title": "Black Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Black Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Set is very well-rounded across the board, providing good &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; absorption and high elemental defenses, all while being one of the lighter sets in the medium category.\nIt is notably stronger against &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;slash&lt;/a&gt; attacks, but is susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;strike&lt;/a&gt; damage. Being a set from the darkened land of &lt;a href=\"Londor\"&gt;Londor&lt;/a&gt;, it offers a very high resistance to the &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Undead Curse&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt;, but is quite vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe set's greatest weakness is that it provides very little &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, comparable to what is normally found on light cloth armor sets. For this reason, its components are generally not optimal gear should one wish to wield large &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; weapons."}
