{"id": "53101", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53101", "title": "Black Witch Set", "text": "The\u00a0Black Witch Set\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Black Witch robe boasts some of the best elemental defenses in game, with its &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; being the highest, and its Fire damage only falling short of the &lt;a href=\"Hexer%27s%20Set\"&gt;Hexer's Set&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Set\"&gt;Chaos Set&lt;/a&gt; by a mere 2 points. It also provides impressive physical defenses for it's weight. \nThe Black Witch Hat has exceptional &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; defense, high elemental defense, decent status resistances, and average physical defenses for its weight and classification. However, its hat allows for an extra &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot.\nThe Black Witch Domino Mask has exceptional &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; defense, high elemental defenses, decent status resistances, and average physical defenses for its weight and classification. It also boasts a minor damage bonus to magic (between 2.5-3%), but lowers maximum &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; by roughly 15%.\nThe Black Witch Veil has exceptional &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; defense, high elemental defenses, decent status resistances, and average physical defenses for its weight and classification. However, its veil boasts a massive boost to &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance, effectively making the wearer immune to being cursed, although they can still become &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;hollowed&lt;/a&gt; upon death. Only the &lt;a href=\"Vendrick%27s%20Blessing\"&gt;blessed&lt;/a&gt; crowns from completing all three of the DLCs and acquiring the &lt;a href=\"King%27s%20Crown\"&gt;King's Crown&lt;/a&gt; can grant total curse and hollowing immunity."}
