{"id": "45610", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45610", "title": "Blacksmith's Hammer", "text": "The\u00a0Blacksmith's Hammer\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nCan be obtained by killing\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Lenigrast\"&gt;Blacksmith Lenigrast&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlternatively, he will give it to you if spend 8000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; reinforcing armor/weapons, and exhaust his dialogue.\nCharacteristics.\nDespite its relative short length, the Blacksmith's Hammer is an interesting &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; to use, as it possesses the highest &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; damage of all Hammers in the game. This, combined with its fast 1 handed weak attack &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;, means that players can hit enemies with speed, allowing players to surprise &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;heavier&lt;/a&gt; armor builds."}
{"id": "130518", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130518", "title": "Blacksmith Andre", "text": "Blacksmith Andre is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe is voiced by .\nLocation.\nHe is Found in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, at the end of the hallway that leads to the back of the shrine, sitting at an anvil.\nDescription.\nAndre is a relatively short man, sporting long white hair that is tied back into a long ponytail, and a long white beard. Andre appears to have various scars and burn marks on his upper body and arms, whilst wearing pants, a belt, and gloves. He can always be found sitting at an anvil, forging an &lt;a href=\"Estoc%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estoc&lt;/a&gt; with a hammer. He has a multitude of tools and weapons lying around him. While similar in appearance to &lt;a href=\"Andre%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Andre of Astora&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt;, it is unknown for certain whether or not the Andre found in \"Dark Souls 3\" is the same person. Some theorize that they are different people, but Andre's knowledge of the Giant Blacksmith, and references to knowing him for ages, has led some to believe that they are in fact one and the same. \nAfter exhausting his dialogue, he teaches the \"Hurrah!\" &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;gesture&lt;/a&gt;.\nAndre will reinforce the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;player's&lt;/a&gt; weapons in exchanged for certain types of &lt;a href=\"Upgrade%20Materials%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;titanite&lt;/a&gt;, depending on the player's reinforcement level and &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Types%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;, as well as souls.\nAndre can &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infuse&lt;/a&gt; weapons if the player brings him various coals found throughout the world. Certain coals yield different infusion upgrade paths. Once a weapon is infused, it may still be upgraded by using the type of titanite specific for it. However, the player should take into consideration if infusing a weapon affects it negatively, according to their stats, or if doing so will remove its &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; bonuses.\nIn addition to upgrading and infusing weapons, Andre can repair those that are broken. He cannot repair the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Sacrifice%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Ring of Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt;, though.\nAndre allows the player character to allocate between a standard &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Estus%20Flask\"&gt;Ashen Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt;. For example, if the player has five Estus Flask uses in total, they can choose to have three standard Estus Flasks uses, which recover &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;, and two Ashen Estus Flask uses, which recover &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;.\nFinally, Andre can reinforce the player's &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; to increase its number of uses. In order for Andre to upgrade the Estus Flask, the player must bring him an &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Shard\"&gt;Estus Shard&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the player kills Andre, he will no longer offer any services, unless the player's sins are forgiven at the shrine of &lt;a href=\"Velka%2C%20Goddess%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Velka&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5247", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5247", "title": "Blacksmith Giant Hammer", "text": "The Blacksmith Giant Hammer is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; upon death.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Blacksmith Giant Hammer has low &lt;a href=\"scaling\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; but a high base damage, and still more scaling than any weapon upgraded through the &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;lightning path&lt;/a&gt;, which have no scaling whatsoever. In terms of damage, this hammer will be poor on a regular leveled playthrough due to having split Physical and Lightning AR due to the way this AR is reduced when going through enemy defenses. Coupled with some enemies significant lighting resistance, this weapon will not perform well on all enemies and bosses. \nLike all &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Hammers&lt;/a&gt;, if an attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal. This animation means that this Hammer gains &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29%23Sweet%2520Spot%2520Damage%2520Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; Damage bonus.\nThe Blacksmith Giant Hammer is a popular weapon for SL1 (Soul Level 1) playthroughs, as it can be 2-handed by Level 1 characters, though it is not the best weapon depending on the boss. For a full chart that details what weapons and upgrade paths will be best at SL1 refer to this &lt;a href=\"https%3A//docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Yl8heFp4GOrmyz4omYCbI2LBlJx5sv4CPpaxPH1Q1dg/edit%3Fusp%3Dsharing\"&gt;SL1 Loadouts Sheet&lt;/a&gt;. "}
