{"id": "5246", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5246", "title": "Blacksmith Hammer", "text": "The Blacksmith Hammer is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Andre%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Andre of Astora&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Parish\"&gt;Undead Parish&lt;/a&gt; upon death.\nCharacteristics.\nLike all &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Hammers&lt;/a&gt;, if an attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal. This animation means that this Hammer gains &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Sweet_Spot_Damage_Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; Damage bonus. \n&lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Reinforced%20Club\"&gt;Reinforced Club&lt;/a&gt; will be better in most situations. Both have superior scaling, base damage and don't require as much strength to wield. Killing Andre for this Hammer is a bad idea unless the player is ending their playthrough and have already acquired a +15 weapon. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "131435", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131435", "title": "Blacksmith Hammer (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Blacksmith Hammer is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Untended%20Graves\"&gt;Untended Graves&lt;/a&gt;, lying on &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Andre\"&gt;Andre&lt;/a&gt;'s anvil at the spot where he normally can be found in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nIn comparison to other hammers, the Blacksmith Hammer is virtually identical to the &lt;a href=\"Mace%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt;, although there are a few differences.\nAt base damage, the Blacksmith's Hammer deals 10% less than the Mace, and also has slightly higher &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; requirements. However, as its item description states, it inflicts 10% more stamina damage with each strike, making it unusually adept at breaking the guard of raised &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
{"id": "38583", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38583", "title": "Blacksmith Lenigrast", "text": "Blacksmith Lenigrast is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blacksmiths%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nPlot.\nLenigrast is a tetchy and seclusive blacksmith cursed with &lt;a href=\"undeath\"&gt;undeath&lt;/a&gt;, a trait that can be noticed in the decaying state of his skin. He is first encountered in &lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt; and offers smithing services to the player after retrieving his &lt;a href=\"Lenigrast%27s%20Key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20Hag%20Melentia\"&gt;Merchant Hag Melentia&lt;/a&gt;.\nThough his body has already decayed, memories of his daughter and blacksmithing are all that remain. Lenigrast is first encountered locked out of his shop in Majula. He asks the player to find &lt;a href=\"Lenigrast%27s%20Key\"&gt;his key&lt;/a&gt;, which can be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20Hag%20Melentia\"&gt;Merchant Hag Melentia&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt;.\nHis daughter is &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Trader%20Chloanne\"&gt;Stone Trader Chloanne&lt;/a&gt;, whom he refers to as \"reckless\" like the player for always being in transit. When she arrives at Majula, Lenigrast expresses his relief that she has \"come home\". Chloanne does not recognize him in his &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;ing form and questions whether her father had followed her to &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt;. He also warns the player of &lt;a href=\"Laddersmith%20Gilligan\"&gt;Laddersmith Gilligan&lt;/a&gt;, citing him as an infamous scoundrel who \"always manages to stir up trouble\".\nHe will drop\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%27s%20Hammer\"&gt;Blacksmith's Hammer&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0if killed or give it to the player after spending 8000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; reinforcing equipment.\nBugs.\nThere is a bug that occurs when the player attempts to attack Lenigrast while he is still sitting down outside of his house. Instead of defending himself, he will continue to sit still. This can be fixed by resting at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; and returning to him."}
