{"id": "8556", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8556", "title": "Bloathead", "text": "Bloatheads are &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". They are only found in the \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC.\nLocation.\nBloatheads can be found throughout &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Township\"&gt;Oolacile Township&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Chasm%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Chasm of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;. One is also located on the elevator in the &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Township%20Dungeon\"&gt;Oolacile Township Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThey have oversized arms, webbed fingers and toes, pale skin, a filthy, mutated head, and are often seen twitching uncontrollably in mindless laughter.\nLore.\nBloatheads are the disturbed remnants of the populace of &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;, whose humanity went out of control after the Dark of &lt;a href=\"Manus%2C%20Father%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Manus&lt;/a&gt;, father of the Abyss, overtook them."}
{"id": "10103", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10103", "title": "Bloathead Sorcerer", "text": "Bloathead Sorcerers, also known as Abyss Guards,\u00a0are &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nDescription.\nThere are two kinds of Bloathead Sorcerers: \"normal\" and \"frenzied\". The \"frenzied\" are more aggressive and deal more &lt;a href=\"Magic%20damage\"&gt;Magic damage&lt;/a&gt;. They can be differentiated by their glowing, red eyes.\nLore.\nLike &lt;a href=\"Bloathead\"&gt;Bloathead&lt;/a&gt;s, Bloathead Sorcerers were the former denizens of &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;, corrupted by &lt;a href=\"Manus%2C%20Father%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Manus&lt;/a&gt;'\u00a0influence. However,\u00a0Bloathead Sorcerers are female and were once\u00a0sorcerers."}
