{"id": "150030", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150030", "title": "Blood of the Dark Soul", "text": "The Blood of the Dark Soul (\u6697\u3044\u9b42\u306e\u8840) is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Slave%20Knight%20Gael\"&gt;Slave Knight Gael&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nGive to the &lt;a href=\"The%20Painter\"&gt;Painter&lt;/a&gt; to trigger dialogue between herself and the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nLore.\nThe Painter will thank the player for giving her the blood and states that she will paint a new world with it. She will then ask the player to state their name. The player is given the option of saying their name, or to say that they don't have one. If the player chooses the first option, then the Painter will name the new world after the player. If the second option is chosen, she will comment on how the Ashen One is very much like her, and chooses to simply name the world \"Ash\".\nRegardless of the option chosen, the Painter will say that the world will \"be a cold, dark and very gentle place,\" and how it will make someone a goodly home.\nTalking to her after this event will trigger a small piece of extra dialogue where she wonders when &lt;a href=\"Slave%20Knight%20Gael\"&gt;Gael&lt;/a&gt; will return, unaware of his death at your hands.\nThis has no effect on the &lt;a href=\"Endings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ending&lt;/a&gt; of the game."}
{"id": "3997", "revid": "357157", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3997", "title": "Bloodbite Ring", "text": "The Bloodbite Ring is a resistance-building &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nObtaining.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Oswald%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Oswald of Carim&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Parish\"&gt;Undead Parish&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s.\nGeneral information.\nThe Bloodbite Ring multiplies base &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; resistance (via &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt;) by 4. The ring does not affect, nor it is affected by, resistance granted from armor. However, it does stack with weapons such as the &lt;a href=\"Bloodshield\"&gt;Bloodshield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%27s%20Halberd\"&gt;Gargoyle's Halberd&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%20Tail%20Axe\"&gt;Gargoyle Tail Axe&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nThe Bloodbite Ring is of limited use in PvE due to the small amount of monsters that cause significant &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up, but can be useful when equipping the &lt;a href=\"Lifehunt%20Scythe\"&gt;Lifehunt Scythe&lt;/a&gt;. It is marginally more useful in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, where bleed weapons such as &lt;a href=\"katanas\"&gt;katanas&lt;/a&gt; can be popular.\nBecause it grants a bonus to the maximum amount of the bleed meter, it gives the illusion that the player's bleed meter fills up when equipping the ring. The phenomenon is explained in detail on the &lt;a href=\"buildup\"&gt;buildup&lt;/a&gt; page."}
{"id": "52308", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52308", "title": "Bloodbite Ring (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Bloodbite Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe regular version can be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Cromwell%20the%20Pardoner\"&gt;Cromwell the Pardoner&lt;/a&gt; for 7,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;. It can also be received from &lt;a href=\"Saulden%2C%20the%20Crestfallen%20Warrior\"&gt;Saulden, the Crestfallen Warrior&lt;/a&gt; after achieving the first level in the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinels\"&gt;Blue Sentinels&lt;/a&gt; covenant in the edition.\nThe +1 version can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;Dragon's Sanctum&lt;/a&gt; area in &lt;a href=\"Shulva%2C%20Sanctum%20City\"&gt;Shulva, Sanctum City&lt;/a&gt;."}
