{"id": "133778", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133778", "title": "Bloodlust", "text": "The Bloodlust (\u8840\u72c2\u3044 \"Chikuruoshii\", Blood-Crazed) is a &lt;a href=\"Katanas%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;katana&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAwarded for attaining Rank 1 in the &lt;a href=\"Mound-makers\"&gt;Mound-makers&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nIn terms of visible statistics, Bloodlust is an unimpressive katana that is outperformed by most other options, particularly as it cannot be &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt;. As such the weapon is reliant on its &lt;a href=\"Bloodlust%20%28skill%29\"&gt;namesake&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;. When activated, the user stabs themselves with the sword, taking damage and inflicting 200 points of &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up in exchange for a 30% increase to its physical damage as well as an increased bleed buildup. The buff lasts for about 45 seconds and allows Bloodlust to deal more physical damage than any other katana in the game, even rivaling the &lt;a href=\"Frayed%20Blade\"&gt;Frayed Blade&lt;/a&gt; in raw attack power.\nHowever, the necessity of having the buff active at all times can make the weapon risky to use, particularly against opponents that can apply bleed themselves. Furthermore, while the Bloodlust skill can deal massive damage if it hits an enemy behind the user this tactic is extremely impractica. and as such the sword gives up the flexibility offered by attack skills like &lt;a href=\"Hold\"&gt;Hold&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Darkdrift%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Darkdrift&lt;/a&gt; in favor of its higher damage output. With this in mind it may be prudent to have a backup weapon when using Bloodlust, particularly in a &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; scenario.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;\nTrivia.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "139864", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=139864", "title": "Bloodlust (skill)", "text": "Bloodlust is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen performed, the user flips the sword, grabs the blade, and proceeds to stab themselves with it. The user then pulls it out, giving the weapon 30% more &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage as well as an additional &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up for 50 seconds. As the buff animation takes a bit over 4 seconds, the effective duration will be about 45 seconds.\nThe skill requires 10 &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; to perform (8 &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Ring\"&gt;Farron Ring&lt;/a&gt; is equipped) and causes 200 &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up on the user as well as &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage, which is based on the user's maximum &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; and ignores both defenses and absorption.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nDue to the sword being un-buffable, this skill is crucial in order to maximize its damage potential. Due to it being a physical buff, it can be effective against all manner of enemies that may have strong elemental resistances. However, care must be taken when combating enemies that inflict Bleed build-up, as even a single hit can greatly damage the player following an activation. In such cases, immediate consumption of a &lt;a href=\"Bloodred%20Moss%20Clump%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bloodred Moss Clump&lt;/a&gt; may be useful.\nOnline gameplay.\nThe additional Bleed buildup and bonus Physical damage can be extremely helpful when combating other players, particularly in areas where there are other sources of bleed (such as if they've been inflicted with the maggot status effect by various enemies in &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;). However, care must be taken as opponents may have their own Bleed-inflicting weaponry equipped, such as &lt;a href=\"Kukri\"&gt;Kukri&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Gnaw\"&gt;Gnaw&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Splintering%20Bolt\"&gt;Splintering Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s, all of which can easily bleed the user out after they activate the buff. As above, immediate consumption of a Bloodred Moss Clump after buffing can be very helpful."}
{"id": "6100", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6100", "title": "Bloodred Moss Clump", "text": "Bloodred Moss Clumps are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nReduces &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; to zero build-up\u00a0upon consumption. Generally not as useful as &lt;a href=\"Purple%20Moss%20Clump\"&gt;Purple Moss Clump&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"Blooming%20Purple%20Moss%20Clump\"&gt;Blooming Purple Moss Clump&lt;/a&gt;s, as situations where there are both Bleed build-up and time to consume an item without getting punished for it is exceedingly rare, as is the Bleed build-up effect itself."}
{"id": "136568", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=136568", "title": "Bloodred Moss Clump (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Bloodred Moss Clumps are consumable in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nBloodred Moss Clumps are used to remove &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; buildup. They can also remove the maggot debuff from the player's body."}
{"id": "2471", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2471", "title": "Bloodshield", "text": "The Bloodshield is a &lt;a href=\"medium%20shield\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Bloodshield is acquired from a corpse in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;, near an &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Dragon\"&gt;Undead Dragon&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Bloodshield boosts all base resistances by 50%. It has poor &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, and is therefore not very useful as a general purpose &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, but is best used when the player needs additional resistance against &lt;a href=\"status%20effects\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis shield has medium deflection and normal &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; speed. The &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; is 24.\nResistance Defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of &lt;a href=\"status\"&gt;status&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking."}
{"id": "20523", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20523", "title": "Bloodstain", "text": "Bloodstains are a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThere are two types of bloodstains in Dark Souls: those left by the player, and those left by other players online. When a player &lt;a href=\"Death\"&gt;dies&lt;/a&gt;, a bloodstain containing all their lost &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; and \"&lt;a href=\"Humanity%20Mechanic\"&gt;liquid humanity&lt;/a&gt;\" is placed at a location roughly five seconds prior to their death.\u00a0\nWhen a player dies as a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%23Red%20Phantoms\"&gt;red phantom&lt;/a&gt;, the bloodstain is left on the exact location the player left their world, just before the loading screen.\u00a0\nTouching one's bloodstain recovers previously earned souls and humanity. Touching a bloodstain left by another player reveals their &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;spirit&lt;/a&gt;, which enacts the last ten seconds of their life. In this way a player new to an area can take advantage of the mistakes of other players. It is only possible to examine one bloodstain at a time."}
