{"id": "136945", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=136945", "title": "Blooming Purple Moss Clump (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Blooming Purple Moss Clumps are consumable in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nThe Blooming Purple Moss Clump will both reduce the build-up of, and cure, &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56034", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56034", "title": "Blossom Kite Shield", "text": "The Blossom Kite Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Blossom Kite Shield is found in a chest in the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Vammar\"&gt;Memory of Vammar&lt;/a&gt;, past the large alleyway with &lt;a href=\"Giant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Giants&lt;/a&gt; and Royal Soldiers fighting, off to the left before entering the broken building.\nScholar of the First Sin.\nIn \"\", the shield can be found on a corpse on the far left wall of the flooded area in &lt;a href=\"Sinner%27s%20Rise\"&gt;Sinner's Rise&lt;/a&gt;, just after exiting the elevator room.\nCharacteristics.\nMuch like the &lt;a href=\"Grass%20Crest%20Shield\"&gt;Grass Crest Shield&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", the Blossom Kite Shield raises &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; regeneration by about 5% (similar to the effects of the &lt;a href=\"Slumbering%20Dragon%20Shield\"&gt;Slumbering Dragon Shield&lt;/a&gt;), and it stacks with the &lt;a href=\"Chloranthy%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Chloranthy Ring&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Green%20Blossom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Green Blossom&lt;/a&gt;. Like the Grass Crest Shield, it is unremarkable in terms of physical defense, but it does boast high elemental and status resistances.\nWhen infused with &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, this shield will block 100% of all poison damage, making it an attractive addition to any player's arsenal when traversing &lt;a href=\"The%20Gutter\"&gt;The Gutter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Black%20Gulch\"&gt;Black Gulch&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, the innately-high &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; status reduction makes it a suitable choice against the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Stalker\"&gt;Dark Stalker&lt;/a&gt;s found in &lt;a href=\"No-man%27s%20Wharf\"&gt;No-man's Wharf&lt;/a&gt;.\nDespite increasing &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stamina regeneration&lt;/a&gt;, the weight penalty from having it equipped tends to negate the amount added unless having a relatively high Maximum Equip Load."}
{"id": "12323", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12323", "title": "Blowdart Sniper", "text": "Blowdart Snipers are non-respawning in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nThey are encountered in &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nAs their name would suggest, Blowdart Snipers have very long range. In addition, they're hard to detect and make little noise. Their darts inflict &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; buildup."}
{"id": "29577", "revid": "35416778", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29577", "title": "Blowdart Sniper Club", "text": "The Blowdart Sniper Club is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; which was &lt;a href=\"Removed%20Content\"&gt;removed&lt;/a&gt; from the final release of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nThe Blowdart Sniper Club was, as the name states, intended to be an alternate weapon for the &lt;a href=\"Blowdart%20Sniper\"&gt;Blowdart Sniper&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;, for when the player was in melee range, and as a result, was also intended to be one of their dropped items.\nThe most interesting aspect of this weapon is that the Blowdart Snipers are able to use it when forcibly equipped through third-party programs; that is, the weapon has its own &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; when they attack with it. However, the only reason it is not used by the Blowdart Snipers is because, within their programming, they are defined as being &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; who cannot switch weapons.\nDue to its nature as cut content, the Blowdart Sniper Club is simply a texture in the game files. This means that even if the player modified their save file, it would not have its own stats anyway, as an existing weapon's model has to be overridden in order to 'obtain' it. Hence, the weapon can only be seen by those who are modifying the game to use its model."}
