{"id": "11194", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11194", "title": "Blue Drake", "text": "Blue Drakes, also known as Drakes or Wyverns, are &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nSeveral can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20Drakes\"&gt;Valley of Drakes&lt;/a&gt;, in front of the sealed gate leading to &lt;a href=\"New%20Londo%20Ruins\"&gt;New Londo Ruins&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThey have blueish indigo scales, are capable of flight, and strongly resemble the &lt;a href=\"Hellkite%20Dragon\"&gt;Hellkite Dragon&lt;/a&gt;, however, Blue Drakes are smaller and breathe &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategies.\nA good way to fight Blue Drakes is to have a shield that can block at least 80 percent Lightning damage.\nStaying in close-quarters with a Blue Drake will trigger its melee attack until the player moves far enough away. Moving behind it can cause it to fly in the air and shower an &lt;a href=\"area%20of%20effect\"&gt;area of effect&lt;/a&gt; Lightning attack. One should also be cautious of straying too far away, as the majority of their attacks exceed their lock-on distance. This can cause players attempting to backpedal out of the way of an attack to spontaneously turn around and cease blocking.\nIt is safer to fight these creatures one by one in an open area.\nEnemy information.\nDrops.\nWyverns are the only respawning enemies that drop &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scale\"&gt;Dragon Scale&lt;/a&gt;s, making them the only constant source for this item for offline players."}
{"id": "6937", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6937", "title": "Blue Eye Orb", "text": "The Blue Eye Orb is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGranted after joining the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon\"&gt;Blade of the Darkmoon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nUsing the Blue Eye Orb allows the player to attempt to invade the world of players that have been &lt;a href=\"Indictment\"&gt;indicted&lt;/a&gt;. The player must be in the Blades of the Darkmoon covenant to use the Blue Eye Orb; unlike the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Eye%20Orb\"&gt;Red Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt;, reversed hollowing is not required and a &lt;a href=\"bloodstain\"&gt;bloodstain&lt;/a&gt; is not left behind if the Blade of the Darkmoon is defeated. Upon defeat of the guilty player, the Blade of the Darkmoon will receive a &lt;a href=\"Souvenir%20of%20Reprisal\"&gt;Souvenir of Reprisal&lt;/a&gt; and the host's sin is reduced by 1."}
{"id": "57192", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57192", "title": "Blue Flame", "text": "The Blue Flame\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Leydia%20Pyromancer\"&gt;Leydia Pyromancer&lt;/a&gt;s of the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Blue Flame, like &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Wisdom\"&gt;Staff of Wisdom&lt;/a&gt;, is only able to cast &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt; (but not &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;Hexes&lt;/a&gt;), and is essentially a fusion between a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Staves\"&gt;Staff&lt;/a&gt;, much like the &lt;a href=\"Mace%20of%20the%20Insolent\"&gt;Mace of the Insolent&lt;/a&gt;, which is a combination of a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Hammer&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Chimes\"&gt;Chime&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs a Straight Sword it is a reliable weapon, despite lacking any strong attacks, which are replaced with casting magic; and its capabilities as a catalyst for sorceries are very moderate as well, but the fact that it is a fusion of both means it can be attractive towards players who prefer a more versatile approach to combat, being able to deal consistent damage across all platforms of range, without switching between weapons. Attacking enemies from a distance to chip away at their health while also luring them towards the player to engage in close quarters is a reliable strategy.\nOne advantage it does have over staves, is the fact that its casting height is much lower than other staves, this means that while in tight or irregular spaces, like corridors, most staves may hit the environment instead of the enemy when casting a spell, the Blue Flame, however, will not.\nThe Blue Flame is upgradeable through &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;, but because its rather low scaling will never be increased through upgrading, it is suggested to &lt;a href=\"Infusion\"&gt;infuse&lt;/a&gt; it with Magic. This will increase its magic damage as well as its scaling with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. There is little reason to keep this weapon uninfused, if the player intends to use it. Do note that infusion with &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; barely decreases the sword's base stats while ironically providing better scaling for Magic. However, if one wishes to maximize the spell power of this weapon, they are still better off infusing it with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;. \nWhile the spell buff on this weapon is respectable enough, it has the unique advantage of being temporarily increased further through magic weapon buffs such as &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Magic%20Weapon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Crystal Magic Weapon&lt;/a&gt;. A fully upgraded Magic Blue Flame with Crystal Magic Weapon applied has the strongest spell buff after &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Wisdom\"&gt;Staff of Wisdom&lt;/a&gt;. As such, if a player wishes to run Magic Blue Flame with Crystal Magic weapon as their main catalyst, it is recommended that they buff their magic duration as much as possible (&lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;and &lt;a href=\"Northwarder%20Set\"&gt;Northwarder Set&lt;/a&gt;) since Crystal Magic Weapon has limited uses. \nIts innate magic damage combined with being infusable and buffable gives the rather unique combination of using the stronger buff to innate magic damage of &lt;a href=\"Aromatic%20Ooze\"&gt;Aromatic Ooze&lt;/a&gt; to grant strong sorcery damage even at low levels of Intelligence. "}
{"id": "58991", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=58991", "title": "Blue Knight's Halberd", "text": "The Blue Knight's Halberd is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe only way to obtain the weapon is by killing &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinel%20Targray\"&gt;Blue Sentinel Targray&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Blue Knight's Halberd has balanced\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; scaling and uses the standard halberd moveset. As such, it is a good option to the &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt; for dexterity builds.\nIt is upgraded with\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;, and loses only minute amounts of its base damage when infused."}
{"id": "46385", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46385", "title": "Blue Seal", "text": "The Blue Seal\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGiven by &lt;a href=\"Saulden%2C%20the%20Crestfallen%20Warrior\"&gt;Saulden, the Crestfallen Warrior&lt;/a&gt; after he initiates the player into the &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;. Speaking to him several times is required before he will ask whether the player would like to join.\nEffect.\nEquipping the Blue Seal will increase the player's total HP by 3%.\nNotes.\nWearing the ring is not required to summon Blue Sentinels, the player only needs to join the covenant."}
{"id": "172760", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=172760", "title": "Blue Sentinel", "text": ""}
{"id": "38582", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38582", "title": "Blue Sentinel Targray", "text": "Blue Sentinel Targray is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". He's voiced by , who previously voiced &lt;a href=\"Solaire%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Solaire of Astora&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vamos\"&gt;Vamos&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nAn apostle of the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinels\"&gt;Blue Sentinels&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;, Targray demands a rigid discipline both from himself and fellow covenant members when acting as a guide (likely for &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt; covenant members) from the covenant. While devoting his life to his mission, his actions and words occasionally denote a narrow mind.\nHe will be dismissive of players who have not yet acquired a &lt;a href=\"Token%20of%20Fidelity\"&gt;Token of Fidelity&lt;/a&gt;; this item can be earned in online play while participating as a white phantom or can be found along with a &lt;a href=\"Pharros%27%20Lockstone\"&gt;Pharros' Lockstone&lt;/a&gt; on a broken pillar in &lt;a href=\"Huntsman%27s%20Copse\"&gt;Huntsman's Copse&lt;/a&gt;, near the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20Approach\"&gt;Bridge Approach&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "44381", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44381", "title": "Blue Sentinels", "text": "The Blue Sentinels is a &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\", devoted to protecting members of the &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt; covenant and invading worlds of those who have &lt;a href=\"Sin%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sinned&lt;/a&gt;. The covenant operates much like the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon\"&gt;Blade of the Darkmoon&lt;/a&gt; covenant from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nRequirements.\nMust speak with &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinel%20Targray\"&gt;Blue Sentinel Targray&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Cathedral of Blue&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Token%20of%20Fidelity\"&gt;Token of Fidelity&lt;/a&gt; in your inventory.\nHow to join.\nTalk to Blue Sentinel Targray. He is located in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Cathedral of Blue&lt;/a&gt;, directly after the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Dragonslayer\"&gt;Old Dragonslayer&lt;/a&gt; boss fight. The player must have successfully assisted another player in killing a boss by using the &lt;a href=\"White%20Sign%20Soapstone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;White Sign Soapstone&lt;/a&gt; and receiving a Token of Fidelity or find the one in &lt;a href=\"Huntsman%27s%20Copse\"&gt;Huntsman's Copse&lt;/a&gt; along with a &lt;a href=\"Pharros%27%20Lockstone\"&gt;Pharros' Lockstone&lt;/a&gt; on a broken pillar or the one dropped by the red phantoms if you use a ascetic on the blue cathedral bonfire or the heide's ruin bonfire (both drop one), otherwise Blue Sentinel Targray will simply dismiss the player. Additionally, using a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Ascetic\"&gt;Bonfire Ascetic&lt;/a&gt; in Heide will allow red phantom Blue Sentinels to spawn that drop three Tokens of Fidelity.\nLore.\nThe Blue Sentinels are a group that descended directly from the original &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon\"&gt;Blade of the Darkmoon&lt;/a&gt; covenant that served &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Sun%20Gwyndolin\"&gt;Dark Sun Gwyndolin&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;. Because of this they were part of the group that at some time left the city of the gods and &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt; and reached &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt;, founding the civilization of &lt;a href=\"Heide%27s%20Tower%20of%20Flame\"&gt;Heide&lt;/a&gt; as Heide's &lt;a href=\"Old%20Knight\"&gt;Knights&lt;/a&gt;\nstill possess the &lt;a href=\"Cracked%20Blue%20Eye%20Orb\"&gt;Cracked Blue Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt;s, the worn remains of the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Eye%20Orb\"&gt;Blue Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt;s that were granted to the &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Blade\"&gt;Blades of the Darkmoom&lt;/a&gt; that served Gwyndolin to mete out the vengeance of the gods at the times of Anor Londo\nThey shared their origin with that of the &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt;, which was not a developed religion but a humble prayer that spread naturally among those seeking help, but which eventually grew to the point that a huge &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Cathedral of Blue&lt;/a&gt; was built in the heart of the city and that the Blue Sentinels used as their headquarters. The Blue Sentinels served the same role of the organization they originated from and thus were tasked with defending the apostles of Blue from evil spirits by traveling between space and time thanks to the &lt;a href=\"Cracked%20Blue%20Eye%20Orb\"&gt;Cracked Blue Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt;s, the remnants of the ancient &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Eye%20Orb\"&gt;Blue Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt;s. The victorious knights would be rewarded with miracles from the ancient gods of Anor Londo like &lt;a href=\"Wrath%20of%20the%20Gods%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Wrath of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bountiful%20Sunlight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bountiful Sunlight&lt;/a&gt; that had been lost or jealously guarded elsewhere in Drangleic, implying that they had inherited a strong relationship with the knowledge of the culture of the gods of Lordran.\nAt some point Heide was destroyed due to the rise of the sea levels the city faced and most of it ended up subsumed by the water, the city became a pile of unsafe submerged rubble but the upper part of the city and the Tower of Flame continue to exist and host the headquarters of the Blue Sentinels with &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinel%20Targray\"&gt;Targray&lt;/a&gt;at its command. The organization would continue to exist to protect the members of the Way of Blue, testing the adventurers who arrived in Heide and were confronted by the remaining &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Knight\"&gt;Heide Knight&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Old%20Knight\"&gt;Old Knight&lt;/a&gt;s.\nand the Cathedral of Blue was defended by an &lt;a href=\"Old%20Dragonslayer\"&gt;Old Dragonslayer&lt;/a&gt; as the ultimate challenge before reaching the leader of the covenant.\nDespite Heide's fall, the Blue Sentinels continued to exert enormous influence in countries near Drangleic. For example in &lt;a href=\"Volgen\"&gt;Volgen&lt;/a&gt;, a city ruled by the clerics of the Way of Blue, the Sentinels possess great power and have the right to decide who can run a shop through their blessing."}
{"id": "131383", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131383", "title": "Blue Sentinels (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Blue Sentinels is a &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHow to join.\nThe covenant item is received by talking to &lt;a href=\"Horace%20the%20Hushed\"&gt;Horace the Hushed&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices%23Bonfires\"&gt;Halfway Fortress&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;, or at &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; after defeating the &lt;a href=\"Deacons%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Deacons of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;. He will also drop the item if he is killed.\nBenefits.\nThe Blue Sentinels are a covenant (along with the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Blade of the Darkmoon&lt;/a&gt;) that puts special emphasis on aiding players in the &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt; covenant that have been invaded.\nWith the covenant item equipped, the player will be automatically summoned to the world of a Way of Blue Adherent who has been invaded by a red or purple dark spirit. After being summoned, the player, now a blue spirit, must protect the host and defeat the invader to receive a &lt;a href=\"Proof%20of%20a%20Concord%20Kept\"&gt;Proof of a Concord Kept&lt;/a&gt; before returning to their world. Alternatively, they can successfully escort the host to the boss of the area.\nRewards.\nOnce the player reaches &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, they may talk to &lt;a href=\"Company%20Captain%20Yorshka\"&gt;Company Captain Yorshka&lt;/a&gt; and become a Blade of the Darkmoon, provided that they have obtained the &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkmoon Loyalty gesture&lt;/a&gt;. Proofs may be turned in to Yorshka in exchange for rewards. \n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "138603", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=138603", "title": "Blue Sentinels (item)", "text": "The Blue Sentinels is a &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nEquip to pledge oneself to the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinels%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Blue Sentinels&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;. Summoning takes place automatically while this item is equipped."}
{"id": "2981", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2981", "title": "Blue Tearstone Ring", "text": "The Blue Tearstone Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Blue Tearstone Ring is found in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt;, to the right and downward from the trio of &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Soldier\"&gt;Hollow Soldier&lt;/a&gt;s before the &lt;a href=\"Taurus%20Demon\"&gt;Taurus Demon&lt;/a&gt;. It is guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt; wielding a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Sword\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is also possible to reach the ring by rolling off the side of the stone bridge near the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. However, this can be difficult to pull off, and it puts the player in direct view of the Black Knight, so that path is generally not worth taking.\nGeneral Information.\nBoosts defense by 50% when the wearer has less than 20% health remaining.\nOverview.\nThe Blue Tearstone Ring is a somewhat situational ring, as its purpose is to prevent death, yet it only activates when the wearer is already severely damaged.\nHowever, medium-armored players with a moderate amount of &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; may find some use in the early-to-mid stages of the game, as the ring is excellent for reducing the damage taken from low-damage attacks, such as the crossbow bolts fired by &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Soldier\"&gt;Hollow Soldier&lt;/a&gt;s, or the attacks of &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Foliage\"&gt;Demonic Foliage&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "65957", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=65957", "title": "Blue Tearstone Ring (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Blue Tearstone Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"\nEffect.\nIncreases &lt;a href=\"defense\"&gt;defense&lt;/a&gt; by 35% when &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; goes below 30%."}
{"id": "130377", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130377", "title": "Blue Tearstone Ring (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Blue Tearstone Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric\"&gt;High Wall of Lothric&lt;/a&gt;. The ring is given to the player by &lt;a href=\"Greirat%20of%20the%20Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Greirat&lt;/a&gt; after he has been freed from his cell and upon agreeing to help him (&lt;a href=\"Cell%20Key\"&gt;Cell Key&lt;/a&gt; required).\nEffect.\nBoosts all damage absorption by 20% when &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; is below 20%.\nUsage.\nThis ring hardly seems effective or useful, given that most enemies will be able to still kill a player who is under 20% &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; with one hit. Still, this ring is offered early in the game and may assist new players against blocked arrows from archers."}
{"id": "6015", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6015", "title": "Blue Titanite Chunk", "text": "Blue Titanite Chunks are &lt;a href=\"upgrade%20materials\"&gt;upgrade materials&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nBlue Titanite Chunks can be found in various areas later in the game. They are dropped by the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Golem\"&gt;Crystal Golem&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Cave\"&gt;Crystal Cave&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Butterflies\"&gt;Moonlight Butterflies&lt;/a&gt; in Crystal Cave.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt; and the Halberd wielding Black Knight in the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt; are guaranteed to drop a Blue Titanite Chunk on death.\nTwo can be found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt; on corpses.\nTwo can be found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Great%20Hollow\"&gt;The Great Hollow&lt;/a&gt; on corpses.\nGeneral information.\nBlue Titanite Chunks can be used to &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;reinforce&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; weapons from +6 to +9, and &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; weapons to +4."}
{"id": "6016", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6016", "title": "Blue Titanite Slab", "text": "Blue Titanite Slabs are &lt;a href=\"upgrade%20materials\"&gt;upgrade materials&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nBlue Titanite Slabs are used to upgrade &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;ascended&lt;/a&gt; weapons down the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"upgrade%20paths\"&gt;upgrade paths&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "57458", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57458", "title": "Blue Wooden Shield", "text": "The\u00a0Blue Wooden Shield\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the hole in the wall near &lt;a href=\"Mild-Mannered%20Pate\"&gt;Mild-Mannered Pate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt; that has multiple ballistae aimed at the entrance.\nCharacteristics.\nFor most players, it will only be a temporary holdover for a few rooms until they find the superior &lt;a href=\"Large%20Leather%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Large Leather Shield&lt;/a&gt;, if they even bother using it at all. Its main distinguishing feature is the incredibly low stat requirement and weight, making it one of the few shields that can be used by Soul Level 1 challenge runners."}
